title: grandma's famous pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie crust.
In a large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour filling into prepared pie crust; sprinkle with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set. Cool.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°. Divide dough into halves.
Roll each half 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Place on nonstick or lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until edges are light brown, 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: hopping john
directions: Combine 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons chopped onion and white vinegar.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain and set aside.
Sort and wash dried black-eyed peas and place in a large Dutch oven.
Add 5 1/2 cups water and salt; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 35 minutes.
Heat oil in a small skillet over medium heat.
Add 1 1/3 cups onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and add to peas.

title: white wedding cake
directions: Sift together flour, 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder, and vanilla pudding.
Beat egg whites in another bowl until fluffy and mix in 1 cup sugar (keep cold)!!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with ham.

title: cool and creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and peel, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping; chill.
Layer fruit in 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with cream cheese mixture and nuts. Chill.

title: atlantic city salt water taffy
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a large saucepan.
Add syrup, butter, water and salt.
Cook rapidly until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour into lightly buttered shallow pan.
Let stand undisturbed until cool enough to handle.
Sprinkle vanilla over candy.
(Add nuts, if desired.)
Pull until white and glossy.
Lay on waxed paper in long rope and cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil yams until fork pierces easily; peel.
Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Add a little more sugar and nutmeg to suit your taste.

title: cookies
directions: Mix the eggs, butter, flour and milk.
Put in bag of chips. Put on cookie sheet.
Put in oven for 3 minutes at 15° Fahrenheit. Cool them, put in dish and eat.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix together sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chop and dredge chopped dates in additional flour and mix with pecans. Add to batter.
Bake in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until springy.
Cool in pan and cut.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add honey, butter and yogurt, mixing well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into carrot mixture.
Pour mixture into oiled 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat taco soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, saute onions in water until tender. Add all ingredients, except tortilla chips.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken caruso
directions: In saucepan, heat chicken broth to boiling.
Add macaroni; cook 10 minutes, or until tender.
Do not drain.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add green pepper and onion; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in macaroni-broth mixture and remaining ingredients.
Heat through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend with butter and pumpkin and beat. Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend and beat for 2 minutes.
Add walnuts and chocolate chips.
Put in tube pan which has been greased on bottom.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: amber's jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over softened cream cheese and mix well.
Place in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Mix in whipped cream, chopped cherries, nuts and oranges.
Return to refrigerator to congeal.

title: charcoal fish
directions: Let charcoal fire burn down to only coals.
Double aluminum foil and form around fish; allow for top to stay open.
Cut sticks of butter into strips about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle fish with lemon pepper and lay strips of butter on top of fish placed over charcoal.
Check every 5 minutes and baste with melted butter until fish gets flaky, usually about 20 to 30 minutes.
Don't overcook or fish will dry out and shrink.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini and onions for 5 to 7 minutes in microwave on High (drain).
Mix sour cream, soup and cheese together.
Add zucchini and onion.
Combine stuffing and melted oleo.
Put 1/2 stuffing in bottom of casserole; put zucchini mixture over stuffing and spread rest of stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: milk punch
directions: Blend milk and sherbet in blender; add soda.

title: spiced peaches or pears
directions: Place fruit in a quart jar that has a lid.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour over fruit in jar and cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve with ham, pork or chicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken approximately 35 minutes.
Retain 2 cups broth. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Prepare 1 package stuffing mix as directed.

title: quick refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add water, buttermilk and melted shortening.
Mix, cover and let set in refrigerator for 12 hours or longer.
Stir and drop into greased muffin cups.
Let rise in muffin pans until double in volume.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook and bone fryer.
Mix and bake.
Serves about 10.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into Pam sprayed Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan.
Remove to serving dish.
Good as is or dust with powdered sugar.

title: hot salad dressing
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except bacon, mayonnaise and Miracle Whip; place in skillet.
First, brown bacon and remove.
Leave some fat.
Cook until thick.
When mixing with potatoes, add 1 tablespoon each mayonnaise and Miracle Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in a colander; squeeze off excess water.
Mix together with eggs, soup and seasonings.
Place into 2-quart casserole dish; cover with Cheddar cheese.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put salt and 2 trays of ice cubes on cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Put on sugar, vinegar and spices.
Heat just to the boiling point. Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend on low heat. Bring to boil. Simmer 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots and cucumber.
Mix gelatin and mayonnaise in top of double boiler.
Heat over hot water to dissolve gelatin. Mix with vegetable mixture.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Spread on sandwiches.
Place in airtight container.
Put wax paper between each layer and on top.
Add moistened paper towel.
Close container and refrigerate.
Stores well.
Mixture may be used for several days.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Divide in half.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Can be wrapped in waxed paper and frozen to slice and bake up to 8 weeks.

title: top ramen salad
directions: Make a day before serving.
Mix together.
Cover tightly. Store overnight.

title: morsel crescent roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls into 16 triangles. Spread cream cheese onto each triangle. Sprinkle with morsels. Roll up as per directions on crescent rolls tube container. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: low calorie meatless lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles until half done.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, cheese, mushrooms and sauce.
Reserve a little cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Serves 4.
Contains 325 calories per serving.

title: cream coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Punch holes in cake.
Mix the milk and cream of coconut; pour over cake.
Let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip, then add coconut to Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Drain
pineapple;
reserve
syrup.
Combine
syrup with brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, tomato paste, cinnamon stick and
salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Let stand 20 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Stir in turkey, green pepper strips, tomato
wedges and pineapple.
Cook until hot.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook butter, mushrooms, green pepper and onions for 5 minutes in medium saucepan. Slowly add flour. Cook until mixture is simmering. Remove from heat. Stir in milk, broth and mushroom liquid. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Add drained chicken. Heat through and serve over biscuits, noodles or rice.

title: mushroom marinade
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat with a fork. After thoroughly mixing marinade, place chilled and drained mushrooms in the bowl with marinade.
Leave overnight in bowl and stir a couple of times so that mushrooms will be thoroughly covered and coated with marinade.
Place in quart jar next day and pour marinade over.
Cut stems off mushrooms even with caps.
Drop caps into boiling water (salted) and 1 tablespoon of vinegar.
Take out when water begins to boil again.
Drain and plunge into cold ice water.
Chill and drain before adding marinade.

title: tamale pie
directions: Put tamales in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over tamales.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Let set.

title: noel eggnog pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cut ice cream in 6 chunks; add to gelatin.
Stir until melted.
Chill until partially set, then add nutmeg and flavoring.
Stir in egg yolks; fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture into pie shell and chill until firm.
Top with fluffs of whipped cream; dust with nutmeg.

title: crock-pot banana bread
directions: With electric mixer, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, bananas and vanilla; mix well.
Stir dry ingredients together with nuts, then add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 2 pound coffee can.
Place can inside crock-pot and cover with a paper towel.
Place lid on crock-pot and cook on high setting for 3 to 4 hours or until tests done with toothpick.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook cubed potatoes.
Cover with water.
Add salt.
Cook it until done.
In another saucepan, boil together vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed.
In skillet fry bacon until crisp; crumble bacon in tiny bits.
Save grease.
Drain cooked, cubed potatoes. Add boiling vinegar mixture, bacon bits and grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until potatoes become slushy.

title: succulent sauteed shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Melt butter in chafing dish or skillet; add lemon juice and seasonings.
Saute shrimp in hot herb butter over medium heat 8 minutes or until pink, turning once. Serve hot, preferably on a bed of rice.

title: aunt marie's oatmeal goodies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and blend thoroughly.
Add oats, pecans, raisins and vanilla.
Add flour which has been sifted with cinnamon, soda and salt.
Roll into teaspoon size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down ball with a flour coated fork.

title: salami
directions: Mix all together and form into rolls.
Wrap in heavy foil or double thickness regular foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake on broiler pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Refrigerate for several weeks or can be frozen.
Cool before slicing.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa in a medium saucepan or cast-iron skillet.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk and mix together. Combine dry ingredients to liquids and add butter.
Cook until thick on stove top, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a

large bowl. Combine rest of ingredients in smaller bowl. Add liquid all at once to dry ingredients. Stir with a fork to blend. Do not overbeat. Let stand 30 to 45 minutes. Batter will thicken (if too thick, add a little more milk). Cook on hot griddle.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over this mixture.
Stir water into mixture to combine ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When batter is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in 4 cups flour.
When dough is stiff enough to handle, turn onto floured board and knead 5 to 10 minutes, adding 1 more cup flour as you knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down; shape into loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with margarine for soft crust.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order.
Add mixed flour and soda, making sure flour is mixed in well, then add nuts, apples and water.
Mix until well folded and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts; debone.
Brown the onion with butter; add the 3 cans of ingredients to the onion.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer chicken, Doritos, soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly hot.

title: bo's georgia sawmill gravy
directions: In a skillet, fry sausage patties.
Drain and keep warm.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Blend in flour and brown, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk or water, mixing well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer.
Crumble sausage patties and add to gravy along with salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes. Serve over hot, open-faced biscuits.

title: sauerkraut
directions: In a large pot, saute chopped onion and diced pork.
Turn down heat and add the cabbage, water, sauerkraut and barley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus dish
directions: Blend sugar, salt, dry mustard and paprika.
Add vinegar. Gradually blend in oil and poppy seed.
Pour over asparagus.
Put 1 grated onion on top.

title: holly dolly cookies
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan for crust.
Layer next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic in medium saucepan. Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; boil gently 15 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Melt oleo in large pan.
Mix in sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil until thick (at least 15 minutes).
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Let set at least 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: busy day coconut drop cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in sour milk or buttermilk.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Blend in coconut.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings #2
directions: Boil chicken or hen until tender.
Cool.
Remove skin and debone; set aside.
Combine flour and oleo.
Mix until consistency of pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup of broth (from boiled chicken) or enough to form a soft ball.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into strips and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Return deboned chicken to pan with dumplings and cook until dumplings are tender (about 30 minutes on low).

title: mexican macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni.
Brown ground beef with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix macaroni and beef which has been well drained with grated cheese, chopped onion, green pepper, tomatoes and frozen corn.
Cover and bake in baking dish for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in butter or margarine. Add tomatoes, rice and mushroom soup. Simmer together until rice is fully cooked. Mix in onion, oregano and thyme. While still hot, pour into casserole. Form lattice work pattern with cheese strips on top of casserole and place slice or 2 stuffed olives in each square. Place casserole under broiler just until cheese starts to melt.
EAT AND ENJOY!!

title: peanut pudding torte
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside. Saute beef until brown; drain. Stir tomato sauce, sugar, salts and pepper into meat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture, then repeat layers again. Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and bake about 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Heat oil in wok until very hot.
Drain pork thoroughly and deep fry in hot oil for just 30 seconds.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Pour out all but 3 tablespoons oil. Fry ginger and garlic gently for 30 seconds.
Add all vegetables and stir-fry. Add oyster sauce, salt, pepper and Accent.
Stir-fry until vegetables are cooked but still crunchy.
Serves 10.

title: my dynamite
directions: Saute in margarine until tender the celery, green peppers and onions.
Add hamburg, tomato soup and tomato paste.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add bananas; mix.
Add flour and soda to above mixture; mix well.
Bake in one large or two small greased bread tins at
for one hour for large pan; 45 to 50 minutes for small pans.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add to bread crumbs.
Add beef, seasonings and egg.
Form into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in flour.
Saute in remaining 2 tablespoons of butter about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add stock or cream.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove meat balls to dish.
Thicken gravy with 1 1/2 tablespoons flour blended with equal amount of water.
Pour over meat balls.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Remove bones and pound thin as you can.
Place ham and stick of Swiss cheese on breast.
Roll, tucking in sides to avoid oozing.
Secure with toothpick; dust with flour and dip into beaten eggs.
Cover meat with mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and dressing mix.
Chill one hour.
One hour before serving, fry rolls in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain the meat.
Remove toothpick.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When meat is cooked, place on warm platter. Heat soup and sour cream (do not boil) and serve over chicken rolls.

title: pan bagna
directions: Slice bread in half horizontally.
Rub each half with garlic and dribble with oil.
Add ingredients in layers evenly over bottom half.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion and sausage in a large skillet, stirring to crumble sausage; drain.
Add soup mix, rice, water and almonds, if desired; mix well and simmer 7 minutes.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornbread and loaf bread crumbs.
Add sage and pepper.
Set aside in a large mixing bowl.
Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add onion and celery mixture to bread crumbs and stir.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple, fruit cocktail and oranges.
Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip, sprinkle jello in mixture and fold until well mixed.
Add fruits and mix well.
Place in refrigerator. Nuts may be added if desired.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soups, cheese and Ro-Tel to same sauce.
Layer chicken, Doritos, sauce twice.
Bake covered 15 minutes, uncovered 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add Worcestershire sauce, seasoning, shrimp and pimento.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: *Use non-frozen, if you wish.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze in lined muffin tins. Makes about 18.

title: fresh grilled veggies
directions: Marinate the vegetables in the Italian dressing (cut the onions into suitable size pieces if necessary).
Let them soak for several hours.
Drain the vegetables, keeping the marinade.
Put the vegetables on skewers and grill over warm, not hot, coals until the vegetables are tender.
Turn them and brush with the marinade frequently.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together for easier, more thorough mixing.
Using electric mixer, cream butter in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add both sugars and beat until fluffy.
Mix in egg and vanilla, then peanut butter and melted chocolate.
Mix in dry ingredients, then chocolate chips.

title: squash bake(for dutch oven)
directions: Melt margarine and place in oiled baking dish or directly in Dutch oven.
Place sliced squash and salt in margarine.
Place cheese and then cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for about 10 minutes, until tender to fork.
Do not overcook.
Serves 8.

title: golden corn stuffing bake
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, stuffing, celery and onion. Spoon stuffing mixture into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange chicken over stuffing mixture.
Press each chicken breast lightly into stuffing mixture.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Parboil broccoli and onions in minimal water, drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in vegetables.
Bake in Pam-sprayed 10-inch pie pan or quiche pan.
Bake in center of oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together shortening, oats, brown sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla and spread in well greased 13 x 9-inch pan (no larger).
Bake 10 minutes being careful not to overbake.

title: picadillo with capers
directions: Use a large skillet with cover.
Heat olive oil and brown beef until all red disappears.
Combine onion, green pepper, tomato, garlic, bay leaf, crushed oregano and capers.
Add to meat in skillet, mix well and cook covered for about 10 minutes on moderate heat.
Cut olives into thin rounds. Add to meat together with tomato sauce, Burgundy wine, hot sauce and brown sugar.
Stir well and cook 5 minutes uncovered.

Now add water and mix well, correct seasoning as needed, cover and cook at low heat for approximately 30 minutes, or until most of liquid is absorbed. Serve over long grain white rice and fried plantains.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix jello and sugar.
Add Kool-Aid and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and pour into ice cube trays. Freeze.

title: country-style potato soup
directions: Melt margarine over low heat. Add onion, celery and garlic. Saute, uncovered, 3 minutes. Add potato and pepper.
Saute 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until the potato is tender. Beat in chives.

title: beer batter fried zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and slice 1/4-inch thick, diagonal.
Cover and set aside.

title: crab and cheese won ton
directions: Mix cheese, lemon, crab and onion. Put 1 teaspoon size in a won ton skin and fold up.
Deep fry won tons in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain.

title: caramel pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, vanilla and milk; fold in the whipped topping. Spread half into pie crust. Drizzle with half of the caramel topping. Combine the toasted coconut and pecans; sprinkle half over the caramel. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saut onions in butter in a skillet over medium heat until translucent.
Do not allow onions to burn.
Add flour, and continue to cook for about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Slowly stir in broth.
Add pumpkin, apple juice, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Puree soup in a blender.
Return to sauce pan.
Add cream and heat.
Makes 8 cups.

title: quick shrimp fried rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni
as
directed, set aside.
Heat oil, panfry onions, 1
egg
and
stir in shrimp.
Drain bean sprouts and rinse once.
Combine
all to rice and fry lightly.
Add soy sauce.
Let set until ready to serve.
Easy and good!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin; sift together dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Add water and mix well. Pour into two 8 x 4 x 3-inch well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream and half the cheese together. Put in baking dish. Cover with rest of cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: slimmers
directions: Sift flour, add salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add flakes, peanuts and raisins.
Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir into flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto sprayed cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: quick rolls
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients; let set 5 minutes.
Heat milk to lukewarm; add milk to sugar and oil and add yeast mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients.
This makes a stiff dough.
Knead and let rise until double in bulk.
Make into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 350° until done.

title: crab stuffed baked trout
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean and wash trout and pat dry.
Mix all other ingredients.
Stuff mixture equally into cavity of each trout.
Close cavity with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish sprayed with cooking oil.
Bake covered for approximately 30 minutes or until trout flake easily.

title: orange floats
directions: In each of 5 tall glasses, place 2 scoops orange sherbet. Pour in orange beverage to fill glasses.

title: country hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Roll out and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: crab newburg
directions: Place margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High about 45 seconds or until melted.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in milk gradually.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring every minute until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in crabmeat and wine.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until hot.
Serve over toast.

title: banana mold(yield:  4 to 6 servings)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
When nearly cold but before set, gradually stir in cream.
Peel bananas; mash with fork.
Beat until light and smooth.
Stir lightly but thoroughly into gelatin and cream.
Pour into mold or glass dish; let set.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pan; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Add the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir up fast and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: buttermilk oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak the oatmeal in the buttermilk at least 1/2 hour.
Beat eggs into oat mixture.
Add honey.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix only until blended.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° until barely golden.
Combine pie filling mix and milk in saucepan and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and let cool completely.

title: lutefisk
directions: Melt butter; whisk in flour and salt.
As it thickens, to it add milk slowly and pepper, constantly stirring.
If desired, blend in mustard.
Serve over Lutefisk.

title: stroganoff in a bun
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Cook until heated through.
Serve on a bun.
Makes 16.

title: frozen vanilla custard
directions: Heat milk over boiling water; mix eggs, sugar and salt. Slowly put in hot milk.
Cook over simmering water, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Remove and cool.
Fold in cream and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into cups and freeze until firm.
Serves 6 or more.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: easy irish bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg and sour cream. Combine liquid mixture and dry ingredients and mix by hand just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add raisins and caraway seed. Place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Brush with melted butter.
Make a cross from diagonal corners.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes and at 325° for another 30 minutes.

title: dried beef roll
directions: Cut the dried beef real fine with parsley flakes.
Put 1/2 of the beef and parsley flakes with the cream cheese, then add mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and make into a log roll.
Put remaining dried beef on waxed paper or Saran Wrap, and roll log roll in dried beef.
Put in refrigerator before serving.
Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Put between any kind of crackers.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils; soak in cold water for 2 hours; drain.
Saute onion and celery in olive oil.
Add lentils, 1 1/4 quarts water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomato paste.
Boil, then simmer, covered 1 1/2 hours.
Add vinegar and oregano.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: country sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion and green pepper; drain grease.
Combine other ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Put in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped nuts together and place 3/4 of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to box directions and pour on top of nut mixture.
Mix cream cheese, oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar together.
Spoon on top of cake batter in blobs.
Sprinkle remaining nut mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom of medium muffin pan cups with shortening.

title: tortilla roll-ups(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Mix all but tortillas together.
Spread mixture on tortillas about 1/2-inch thick.
Roll up tortilla.
Freeze for about 30 minutes to make firm.
Slice into 3/4-inch slices to make little discs.
Serve with picante sauce or queso.
Makes great hors d'oeuvres.

title: aunt charlene's hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble ground beef in bottom of large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, salt and pepper. Cover with a layer of sliced potatoes.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over potatoes.
Continue layering with beef, onions, potatoes and soup to the top of the dish.
Bake covered at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake uncovered for last 5 to 10 minutes until browned.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter, add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bring just to boil; reduce heat and add bananas.
Simmer over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Heat rum; pour over bananas. Ignite carefully and allow flames to subside.
Serve banana mixture over ice cream.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine, then flour, milk and eggs into that mixture.
Add coconut and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: May substitute peaches for pineapple and cherries or any fruit pie filling.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients, divide into 10 balls.
Roll out.
Use 2 teaspoons of fruit filling for each pie.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Save 1/2 nuts.
Mix everything together and chill thoroughly. Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix ingredients, except cabbage; cover and chill.
Pour on shredded cabbage for cole slaw.
Can be doubled for large head of cabbage.

title: pastry for double-crust pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in Crisco until it resembles crumbs.
Make a well in the center of the mixing bowl; add the egg, water and vinegar.
Beat with mixer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and mushrooms. Mix onions and mushroom soup. Put mix in casserole dish. Bake with onion rings on top, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: orange nut balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and form into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar and bananas.
Beat in egg.
Mix flour and soda; add to banana mixture.
Melt butter in loaf pan and pour mixture into pan. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, water and undiluted soup together.
Stir in chicken, onion, almonds, green pepper and salt.
Carefully add sliced eggs.
Place in greased casserole dish; top with potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Form into balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Dip each peanut butter ball into the chocolate mixture.
Let dry on wax paper.
The paraffin adds shine to the chocolate coating.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Combine the rest except noodles.
Pour mayo mix over tuna mix; add noodles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish) in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chips, then coconut and nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Chewy chocolatey cookie bars.
Hard to believe, they're such a snap to make.
That's why we call them magic cookie bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: jean's zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk and lemon juice.
Mix together flour, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder; add to butter mixture.
Add zucchini; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the chips on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce jumbles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains, when touched, about 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool. Makes 5 dozen.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Dump all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into two regular sized, 3 medium or 5 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order except cheese. Pour 1/2 batter in greased baking dish. Add 1/2 cheese. Add remaining batter. Cover with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock guacamole
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add green onions and peas; process until well blended.
Add sour cream, salsa and oil; process until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a bowl; cover and chill.
Yields 1 1/2 cups (serving size:
2 tablespoons).

title: scratch pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk before adding to dry ingredients.
Stir while cooking on medium-high heat until near boiling, then reduce to medium until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter and flavoring.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Bring butter and cheese to room temperature.
Mix well, add rest of the ingredients.
Blend and shape into 1 inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper to chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Slice 1/4 inch thick. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add crushed bananas, chopped nuts and milk, in which soda has been dissolved.	Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Fold in vanilla.
Bake in angel food pan at 325° about an hour or until done.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes.
Pour oil, vinegar and vanilla in separate holes.
Pour water over all.
Mix well with fork.
Do not beat. Bake for 30 minutes.
Leave in pan and frost while still warm.

title: crabmeat horseradish spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in crabmeat.
Serve spread with assorted crackers.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: golden knots
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
In a saucepan, heat the milk, butter and remaining water to 110°-115°.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add eggs, salt, 5 cups flour and the remaining sugar; beat until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Divide into thirds; roll each portion into a 14 inch roll. Divide each roll into 14 pieces.
Roll pieces into 9 inch ropes and tie into knots. place the rolls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Zap in the microwave on Full power for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk; spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Drizzle margarine over seasoning.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels until barely moist. Combine broccoli, Ricotta cheese and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Whip butter and sugar until creamy.
Stir in eggs, beat one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla, mix well.
Bake in tube or loaf pan (well greased and floured) at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake leaves sides of pan.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: jumbo shells
directions: Take 6 or 8 nice pieces of chicken, like the thighs, legs and split breasts.
Rinse well in cold water and dry with paper towel. Take in hand and rub well with salad oil.
Lay on a foil lined casserole.
Sprinkle generously with lemon juice and coat with cornflake crumbs on both sides.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes at least or until slightly browned.
Does not need extra, or any, salt.
Serve with noodles and small salad.

title: penguin eggs
directions: Cut black olives in quarters.
Dip in egg white and place 1/4 of olive for each foot of penguin at bottom end of egg.
Place 1/4 of olive upright along either side of upright egg for fins.
Dip each section to be affixed to egg in egg white to make it stick. Attach whole black olive at top with a toothpick for head.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Make crust by following directions, adding the 1/4 cup sugar. In a large bowl, put cheese, sugar, eggs, salt and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Add to crust-lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with chips. Lattice-strip top of pie.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Mix together until soft dough forms. Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stew. Cook uncovered over low heat 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar angel food cake
directions: Combine flour and 1 cup brown sugar.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Gradually add 1 cup brown sugar, beating well until stiff and glossy peaks form.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Add flour mixture in four parts, folding after each addition.
Spoon into ungreased 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.
Invert cake to cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice both cucumbers and onion thin and mix.
Mix all other ingredients together and stir until sugar has dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or more. Place in airtight containers and place in freezer.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Place bread in bottom of baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk in blender; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture on bread.
Brown sausage and spoon over egg mixture.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and cook uncovered at 350° until corn pudding is set in the middle (about 25 minutes).

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine in order.
Add from 6 to 8 cups of plain flour until a wooden spoon stands straight in the middle

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popcorn in a large container or roasting pan.
Keep warm in oven.
Combine water, oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt and cook over medium heat until it reaches firm ball stage (about 250°).
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda, syrup will foam. Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Cook at 250° for 1 hour in oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove popcorn from oven and spread on opened brown paper bag.
Let it sit separated until cooked and not sticky.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Combine orange, lemon, pineapple and apple juices.
Chill for 1 hour.
Then add soda.
Put ice cubes in 4 tall glasses.
Pour mixture over cubes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini, vanilla, nuts, pineapple and raisins.
In separate bowl, put flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; mix and add to wet ingredients a little at a time.
Blend well.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam; put in mix and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake the chocolate fudge cake as directed on mix box.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; cut in half lengthwise.
With sharp teaspoon, scoop out pulp, reserving pulp, to form boats with 1/2-inch walls. Cut small slice off bottom so boats stand without rolling.

title: sweet garlic dill pickles(makes 6 to 7 quarts)
directions: Note:
Three 2 inch pieces of dill stalk equals 1 head.

title: oklahoma millionaires
directions: Mix sugars, oleo and 1 cup milk. Bring to rolling boil and keep it boiling slowly.
Add remaining milk.
Cook to soft ball (234°).

Add vanilla and pecans. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate for several hours. Cut into squares or mash flat. Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip squares into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper. Toothpicks are excellent for dipping candy.

title: lasagna (beef)
directions: Boil noodles until tender (10 minutes).
Fry ground beef in saucepan; pour 1/2 cup sauce in flat baking dish and layer noodles, ground beef, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Continue until last layer is topped with noodles and sauce.
Bake lasagna for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour together.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Cream well.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour equal amounts in both shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: mighty good cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add eggs and beat well after each addition. Add the next 5 ingredients. Pour batter into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Mix well.
Let marinate for several hours.
Place on grill for 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy skillet cook first 3 ingredients until golden, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from
heat
and add soda.
Stir rapidly
and
pour immediately onto well-buttered baking sheet and spread into a thin layer.
Cool and break into chunks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Accent, lemon juice, Season-All and Wesson oil.
Pour over cooked spaghetti and refrigerate overnight.
Add celery, onion, pimento, mayonnaise, bell pepper, olives and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk and flavorings.
Add pecans last.
Beat well.
Pour in a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased with Pam spray. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: glutenburger loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: miracle cherry pie
directions: Combine pie filling, sugar, salt, water and lemon juice in a saucepan, stirring to form a smooth paste, then stir in the undrained cherries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and food coloring.
Cool 5 minutes, then pour into pie shell.
Let stand until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: schezwan chicken
directions: Combine chicken broth, tiger sauce, cornstarch and fish sauce and set aside.
In wok add peanut oil.
Sprinkle Schezwan peppercorns in hot oil.
Add chicken and sprinkle with tamari sauce, quick-fry.
Add liquid and cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions.
After done, crumble up.
Add celery.
Dice tomato; chop onions and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: chicken broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz to hot rice.
Mix until smooth.
Saute onions in butter; set aside.
Pour enough boiling water over frozen broccoli to thaw; drain well.
Add broccoli, chicken and rice mixture to onion and butter; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak to taste.
Brown steak in a small amount of oil.
Remove steak from skillet.
Add flour; brown flour, then add 2 to 3 cups of water and tomato sauce.
Stir until smooth. Put steak back into gravy.
Add bell pepper and onion (either sliced in rings or chopped).
Works great to simmer in electric skillet about 1 1/2 hours at 250° or 300°, or all day in a crock-pot on low.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls
directions: Assemble in the order listed the night before in Bundt pan. Cover with cloth; let sit at room temperature all night.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 2 minutes.
Come out whole. Serve with 2 forks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients when softened at room temperature. Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Stir.
Then mold with wax paper surrounding.
Put nuts around while molding in the wax paper. Refrigerate for approximately 1 hour before eating.

title: sugar-free chocolate pecan pie
directions: Make the pudding as directed; add pecans. Place into baked pie shell and top with a thin layer of Cool Whip.

title: baked spanish sweet onion rings
directions: Peel, slice and separate onions into rings.
Combine crumbs and seasonings.
Mix well.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Spread bean dip over a large serving platter.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and salt.
Spread over bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocado layer. Sprinkle on tomatoes, onions, black olives and cheese.
Store in fridge no longer than 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with nacho chips and enjoy.

title: polish cabbage
directions: Cook onion in melted oleo until tender.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Cook until tender.
Cook noodles as directed; drain and add to cabbage.
Mix well.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix (Osterize) dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Blend for 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken in large shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste occasionally with pan drippings.
Serve over hot noodles or plain rice.

title: dad's clam pie
directions: Put everything except the bread crumbs into saucepan (include juice from clams).
Simmer until peppers and onions are soft (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: squab with apricot sauce
directions: Season squab with salt.
Brown squab, skin side down, in butter in skillet.
Turn, cover and simmer about 35 minutes or until tender.
Remove to warm platter.
Combine broth, apricot nectar and cornstarch.
Add to pan drippings.
Simmer and stir until sauce thickens slightly and bubbles.
Pour over birds.
Serves 4.

title: veggie stuffed potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook and stir carrots, peppers and Italian seasoning in margarine until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add zucchini. Cook and stir until tender, about 1 minute. Carefully cut or pierce tops of potatoes lengthwise and push ends to open.
Spoon vegetable mixture equally into each potato.
Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese party mints
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add flavorings and colorings. Gradually add confectioners sugar, kneading until putty stage. Use rubber molds and pack.
If it sticks, dip mold in cake sugar. Can be frozen and used later.

title: sweet cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour and cornstarch.
Let the dough stand 30 minutes in the refrigerator.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given in large bowl.
Drop by tablespoon and flatten slightly.
Do not overbake.
Let them sit on cookie sheet for a short time before removing to wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: shrimp rice salad
directions: After rice is cooked, add all ingredients listed.
Add enough Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to keep it all together.
Chill for 4 hours or more.
Take catsup and mix in horseradish until it meets your taste.
Chill.
I put this in a ring mold before chilling. Then I set the sauce in the center of it after unmolding and garnish with lemon and tomato wedges.
Serve with your favorite muffins, etc.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Beat shortening; add sugar, then eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Stir soda into sour cream. Alternate, adding flour and sour cream mixtures to the shortening mixture.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Remove when golden brown.
I put a muscat raisin in the center of each cookie before baking.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and onion powder.
Mash potatoes until fluffy.
Add a small amount of milk if necessary.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to use, drizzle melted butter over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour.
Delicious with meat and no gravy is needed.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Add oleo and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over mixture.
Let cool.

title: red snapper veracruz
directions: Arrange fillets in a shallow baking dish; pour lime juice over fillets and sprinkle with salt.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Add tomato and next 4 ingredients; cover and cook 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and reserve broth.
Cook spaghetti and onion in broth.
Debone chicken.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake until flavors combine and cheese melts.

title: two-sauce eggplant lasagna
directions: Using an 8 x 12-inch pan, lightly oil and place fresh pasta sheet in pan.
Spread pesto sauce on each pasta sheet.
Layer grilled vegetables and pasta.
Repeat this process until the pan is filled.
On the final layer, spread pesto sauce.
Garnish with fresh grilled tomato slices.
Cover with foil and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit filled sweet rolls
directions: Cream butter and gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar; mix well. Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add flavoring and flour; mix well.
Spread batter on well greased cookie sheet.
Mark off two inch squares.
Place one tablespoon of pie filling in each square. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While warm, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: egg macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add vegetables, salad dressing and seasonings.
Chop 5 eggs and mix lightly into mixture.
Chill.
Stir in additional salad dressing before serving.
Garnish with the remaining egg, sliced.

title: sweet sour dill chunks
directions: Cut pickles into 1-inch chunks.
To each jar, add 3 to 4 slices onion, 2 pieces celery and 2 heads of dill.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles; seal at once.
Can use after 30 days.
This is enough for 4 quarts.

title: mrs. goodman's spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti as label directs.
Arrange on heated platter; keep hot.
Meanwhile, in hot oil and butter in skillet, saute garlic until golden.
Add parsley, salt and clam liquid.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add snipped clams and simmer 2 minutes. Pour over hot spaghetti.

title: bavarian goulash
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add wet ingredients; beat well. Place in potato ricer and press through into boiling salted water. Cook for about 5 minutes or until they rise to the surface.
Drain and drizzle with butter.
Saute 1/2 cup bread crumbs in butter until brown and sprinkle over top of warm noodles.
Serve with goulash and gravy with chunky applesauce on the side.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a stock pan, add just enough water to cover broccoli, celery and onion; add bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Then add Cheez Whiz and half and half.
Simmer for a little while and serve.
(You can also add a potato, cut up or thicken with a little cornstarch to make it thicker, if desired.)

title: spumoni(italian ice cream)
directions: Combine the ice cream, topping and sugar.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour the mixture into one or more freezer safe pans. Freeze.

title: peppery potato soup
directions: Combine broth, potatoes, onion, celery, flour, pepper and salt in slow cooker; mix well.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 1/2 hours.
Stir in half and half; cover and continue to cook 1 hour.
Remove slow cooker lid.
Slightly crush potato mixture with potato masher. Continue to cook, uncovered, an additional 30 minutes until slightly thickened.
Just before serving, stir in butter.
Garnish with celery leaves, if desired.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Set aside.
Combine water, rice and raisins in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes; stir.
Arrange pork chops over rice; sprinkle with salt.
Cover and microwave at Medium (50% power) for 10 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn after 5 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large skillet melt butter and saute onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add bay leaves and black pepper.
Stir shrimp and saute until shrimp is tender.
In medium-sized pot add stewed tomatoes, crushed finely with blender.
Stir in Creole season and mix well.
Add entire contents of skillet to tomatoes.
Stir well and cover.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve over hot rice.

title: mamie's date nut bread
directions: Cut dates and nuts; add butter and pour hot water over the top.
Beat egg; add sugar, date and nut mixture and flour.	Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake for about 1 hour in 350° oven. Test with a toothpick.

title: sugarless apple cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir well to mix. Sift dry ingredients and beat.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Wrap tightly in foil when cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1 can condensed milk with juice and berries.
Let set 10 minutes.
Mix with Cool Whip, then pour in crust.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients in shallow casserole dish. Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs. Pour melted margarine over crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add a little pineapple juice if too dry.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, add sugar until peaks form.
Add vanilla, fold in chocolate chips and nuts (optional). Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and place in oven.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop ingredients and toss.
Mix Hellmann's mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add to the other ingredients.
Let stand overnight.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Don't brown.
Mix soup and water.
Stir until smooth.
Heat until cheese melts.
Fold in turkey and drain pimiento.
Put 1/2 in large casserole.
Put spaghetti on top. Add remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Make day before.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Add rest of cheese 15 minutes before done.

title: potato casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, melt butter at full power for 1 minute. Chop onion and add to butter. Cover and cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on full power. Combine remaining ingredients except spices.
Cover with parchment/wax paper and cook 6 minutes at full power, stirring gently halfway through cooking. Sprinkle top with dill, parsley and paprika.
Cook, covered, for an additional 6 to 9 minutes.

title: cajun style cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and center
springs back when touched. Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk until warm; add cream cheese and stir until blended.
Spread chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add all other ingredients to soup mixture and spread over chicken.
Lay crescent rolls (unrolled) flat over top and dribble melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
"Good."

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and cinnamon.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add apples.
Stir until well mixed and smooth.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bill's tomato salad
directions: For individual salads, place small amount of lettuce on plate. Top with 3 slices tomato. Add chopped onion and basil. Pour 1 teaspoon olive oil on each tomato. Sprinkle with pepper and let stand at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: florentine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in vinegar, salad dressing and salt and cool until almost firm.
Beat.
Then add spinach (drained), onion, celery and cottage cheese.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on salad greens.

title: brown sugar filled cookies
directions: Cream butter, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Shape into rolls and chill.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Freezing beef makes it easier to slice thinly.
Beef should be sliced thin.
Pour the 1/4 cup soy sauce and sugar over meat. Marinate 1/2 hour.
Chop tomatoes and green peppers in 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in frying pan; add garlic and ginger.
After a minute, remove garlic and add green peppers.
Saute 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, during remaining cooking time, so ingredients will cook evenly.
Add beef and its liquid; saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and blend cornstarch with the 1 teaspoon soy sauce.
Gently stir it in entire mixture.
Cook, stirring gently for a minute or two.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: breakfast oatmeal muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients.
Add to dry mixture.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: scalloped green beans and celery
directions: Cook cut-up celery in water to cover until almost tender. Drain, saving liquid.
Make a white sauce of 4 tablespoons butter, the flour, milk, celery liquid and salt.
When thickened, add shredded cheese to melt, but do not boil.
Butter the crumbs and brown in a greased baking dish, place half the cooked beans, celery and bread crumbs.
Then add the remainder of vegetables and all of the cheese sauce.
Top with buttered crumbs and place in oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown and hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut cheese in cubes.
Slice eggs.
Spread half crackers in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Add layer of cheese, eggs and asparagus and soup alternately until all are used.
Pour milk and 2 tablespoons asparagus juice over all.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over top.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Add enough water to pan to cover potatoes.
Add butter and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Take 2 more tablespoons of butter and mix with enough flour to make crumbs the size of peas.
Add to boiling soup.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli and steam in 1/2 cup water until tender (don't drain).
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and whip.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes on low heat.
Add chicken broth; stir and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli, then half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: pecan-stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise, and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with a fork; add next 7 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon pecan mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands well. Roll into little balls and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl combine flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper; set aside.
In medium saucepan combine water and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and gradually stir in flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Remove; cool 5 minutes.
Use high speed of an electric mixer and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Drop heaping tablespoonful of batter onto a baking sheet (sprayed with cooking spray), mounding slightly in center.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes (golden brown).
Cool.

title: french muffin donuts
directions: Sift flour with 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Combine milk, egg, melted butter and vanilla.
Add liquid ingredients to flour mixture, stirring only until all ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Brush with melted butter and roll in mixture of remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter and pour into cake pan.
In mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, milk and baking powder. Pour this batter on top of melted butter; do not stir.
Pour fruit and juice over batter; do not stir.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken and cook 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasonings with the exception of the paprika.
Drain broccoli and arrange in bottom of a flat greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Shred chicken and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honeymoon salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling point.
Dissolve gelatin in part of soup. Stir cheese into remainder of soup.
Add gelatin mixture, celery and pepper.
When cook, add mayonnaise and put into a mold.
Chill and serve.
Serves 12.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to soften at room temperature.
Combine with remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.
Refrigerate about 1 hour (or overnight).
Shape 3 balls (or can make 100 walnut size). Roll in chopped nuts or chopped parsley.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream brown sugar and Crisco, creaming well.
Blend in unbeaten egg.
Stir in half the dry ingredients.
All the 1/4 cup maraschino cherry juice and 2 tablespoons milk, then stir in remaining dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend in 2 squares melted chocolate, walnuts and maraschino cherries.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut large marshmallows in half.
Place cut side down on hot cookies.
Cool on rack.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: crabmeat creole
directions: Cook rice; rinse and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in small amount of oil.
Add tomatoes; heat.
Add crabmeat; heat. Sprinkle parsley over top.
Serve hot over rice.

title: a meal in one
directions: Cook beans until 1/2 done.
Peel and dice potatoes into beans. Add hamburger.
Peel and cut onion into mixture.
Add parsley flakes, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add beef gravy.
Let cook and serve.
"Great any time."

title: rum sauce(custard-type)
directions: Heat milk; add eggs, sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Be careful to cook on low heat so that custard will not curdle.
Add rum.
Serve with cake or bread pudding.
Rum flavoring may be used instead of rum if desired.
Sauce may be processed in blender or food processor for a smoother texture.

title: congo squares
directions: Stir 2 3/4 cups flour, 2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and salt together; set aside.

title: orange blossom
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend until of sherbet-like consistency.
Spoon into cocktail glasses and serve with short straws.
Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.

Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine powdered sugar, cold margarine, eggs and vanilla. Beat on high speed of mixer for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker crust and chill 1 hour. Slice bananas and dip in pineapple juice (lemon juice) to prevent browning and layer over mixture in pan.
Top with pineapple, then Cool Whip, cherries, pecans and chocolate syrup.
Serves 12.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil all except nuts together until mixture forms soft ball when tested in cold water.
Pour over nuts, and mix well.
Serve when cool.

title: working girl rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, set aside.
Mix sugar, egg and oil.
Add flour and yeast mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in glass bowl; cook on High in microwave 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 1/2 minutes more.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add soda.
Stir and pour on cookie sheet; spread thin.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with beater until smooth.
Cover, then refrigerate.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Brown wieners in oil, putting onion on top of wieners while browning.
After wieners have browned, make a sauce of remaining ingredients.
Pour over wieners and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: sallie knouse's cream puffs
directions: Put the butter in the hot water and boil until butter is melted.
Stir in quickly and all at once the flour.
Remove from burner and beat until smooth.
When cool, stir in the eggs and beat 5 minutes.
Drop from a tablespoon onto buttered tins.
Bake in moderate oven about 25 minutes.
When cold, fill.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and butter.
Add coconut.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.

title: cherry fiesta pie
directions: Cook until thick cherries, pineapple, sugar and nuts.
May want to thicken with cornstarch.
Add jello and cool slightly. Add bananas and pour into baked crust.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix chocolate and sugar together and add milk.
Beat egg yolks and stir in flour, then add to milk mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: crock-pot cheese-broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and saute until glossy. Transfer to crock-pot.
Gradually add flour to cooking pot, stirring constantly, with a whisk or spoon. Add chicken broth and stir until smooth. Add salt, celery, carrots and
broccoli.
Stir to combine. Cover and cook either on low for 6 to 7 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours. Add cheese cubes, stirring until melted.
Add half and half, stirring to blend. Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes or until soup is hot. Reduce heat to low for serving. Garnish individual bowls with croutons, if desired.

title: mama's delicious homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate eggs; mix yolks well.
Add sugar to egg whites; mix well.
Add Cool Whip to yolks.
Mix well.
Pour into a gallon ice cream tub.
Add evaporated and condensed milks, whipping cream and vanilla flavoring.
Finish filling remainder of tub with whole or low-fat milk.
Makes 1 gallon.
(Note:
Using low-fat milk does not make this a low-fat recipe.)
Mix well then freezer up.
Enjoy!

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Then mix all other ingredients together and pour in water.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the sugar and Karo well; microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts; mix and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; mix and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and mix well.
Immediately pour out on a well-buttered cookie sheet and spread out.
Work quickly as it sets up fast.
Cool; break apart.
Enjoy.

title: honey chicken supreme
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken.
Drain oil.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer in covered pan until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Blend paprika, chili powder, garlic salt or powder and flour. Sprinkle mixture on both sides of chicken breasts.
Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil; remove.
Brown chicken breasts, then cook for about 10 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and jar of salsa.
Cover; simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove lid.
Add cheese (enough to cover chicken).
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Bon appetit!

title: randy's real new orleans style cheese straws(for folks)
directions: Beat cheese and butter until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and put through a cookie press.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Hide from spouse and kids until the company arrives!

title: sunshine salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple just enough to melt jello.
Then mix everything together.
Then pour in your salad dish or pan and put in refrigerator.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Rum Glaze.
Just until moistened. Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cups.
Spread Rum Glaze over warm muffins.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat flour, sugar, margarine and salt in large bowl on medium speed until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly in pan.
Bake until light golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Prepare filling.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar, add eggs.
Make a paste of the food coloring and cocoa.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add alternating buttermilk with sifted flour and salt.
Then add vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar.
Hold over the bowl as it foams.
Then blend into the cake mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 1 inch pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack, when cool, split each layer into 2 layers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend butter and flour.
Add broth, milk and water.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, rice, chicken and vegetables.
Pour into a large greased baking dish. Top with crushed potato chips or slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: soup beans and dumplings
directions: Cook beans until done seasoned with meat grease and salt. Pinch biscuits into pieces and drop into beans.
Keep beans at a low boil and stir occasionally.
Cook approximately 8 minutes.
Be sure beans have enough liquid before adding biscuits.

title: mona's brownies
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute, gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Gradually add flour and blend.
Add the nuts and pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread out. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk and sugar.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir completely.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash and onion.
Layer squash and onion, then soup, then crackers, then cheese.
Dot with butter and bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: quick mustard pickles
directions: Pack a quart jar with small pickling cucumbers.
Add the sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Fill the jar with apple cider vinegar.
Shake.
Put in refrigerator and shake occasionally. Leave for 7 days before using.

title: garlic grits souffle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick. Add the butter, cheese and eggs.
Mix well. Place in a buttered dish. Cover with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and use in your favorite recipes.

title: cut the pickles and cut the carrots(macaroni salad)
directions: Chop pickles and carrots. Cook noodles and drain. Cool noodles by running them under cold water. Put all ingredients into a bowl, then top with mustard and dressing. Mix until all is covered and serve.

title: ozark pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir together remaining ingredients and add to above.
Mix well.
Roll into balls size of a walnut and roll in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix together mushroom soup and 1/2 can milk, set aside.
Brown ground beef, drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Lightly grease (13 x 9-inch) dish with margarine or use nonstick spray.
Layer bottom of dish with 6 shells, add 1/2 of ground beef, spread on 1/2 of cream of mushroom.
Top with cheese; layer 6 more shells, add remaining ground beef and cream of mushroom.
Top with with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain meatballs well.
Heat chili sauce and jelly until melted.
Add cooked meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: tin roof
directions: Crush cookies; pat down with melted butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Stir ice cream until creamy. Spread over cookie layer.
Add peanuts. Freeze.
Boil fudge topping 8 minutes, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool. Pour cool fudge sauce over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle baking soda over dates. Add boiling water and let stand until warm. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and date mixture, then flour, salt and vanilla. Lastly, add walnuts. Grease mini loaf pans (makes about 9 loaves) and fill each with batter halfway. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Beat eggs in a mixing bowl until frothy.
Mix in cooking oil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into shallow greased 9-inch casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown the hamburger. Add refried beans and taco sauce.
Cook until bubbly. Fill tortillas with 1/3 to 1/2 cup mixture.
Roll and place in baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over. Top with grated cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Top with sour cream. Makes 10.

title: mock cranberry fruit spritzer
directions: In a large wine glass, pour cranberry apple drink and white grape juice over ice.
Add a splash of club soda.
Garnish with grapes or a lime slice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chili corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Be sure to spray 9 x 13-inch pan well.)
This is really good with barbecue and red beans!

title: tuna-corn chowder
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Mix in curry powder.
Add drained tuna and corn; stir until well distributed.
Heat on medium, stirring constantly, until very hot.
Dilute with some of the hot water if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: tropical storm
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until smooth.
