If desired, garnish with a pineapple chunk and a sprig of mint.
Yields four 6 ounce servings.

title: spinach topping
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine oil and seasonings.
Stir in 1/4 pound of mushrooms, thinly sliced and cook for 5 minutes.
Add 10 ounces of spinach, cut into strips. Cover and cook about 3 minutes or until spinach wilts.
Stir in 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook carrots, celery and onion 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat through.
Ladle into bowls; top with cheese.
Makes 3 1/2 or cups 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: all american cheese  pie
directions: In bowl stir together the crushed cookies and melted margarine until moistened, and press into 8 x 10 pie pan and freeze.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until there are no lumps.
Add water until batter is thin.
Heat griddle or skillet on medium heat.
Put 1/4 cup of batter on griddle.
Turn when pancake starts to make bubbles.
Makes 8 to 12 pancakes.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove and top with French fried onion rings and almonds. Bake for additional 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine soup, milk and pepper. Stir in green beans and 1/2 of onions.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheesy italian tomato and olive salad
directions: Toss and serve chilled on a bed of romaine lettuce.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Wash, drain and halve the cranberries.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine moist ingredients.
Add moist to dry and blend.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Batter may be baked in loaf or muffin pan.
For loaf bake at 325° for 1 hour.
For muffin bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel, cool and cube. In melted margarine, saute onions and green pepper for 1 minute. Add pimentos, seasonings and flour.
Blend in milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind the first 2 ingredients together.
Add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain again.
Be sure all water is off or relish will be thin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.
Watch and stir often while cooking.
Seal in pint jars.

title: mounds bars
directions: Melt butter; mix with graham crackers.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash the beans and soak overnight. Drain the beans and place in a large pot. Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces and brown in a little oil. Remove sausage and saut onion, celery and green pepper in drippings. Add all ingredients to the beans. Cover with water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook slowly until beans are tender. Serve over rice.

title: brunch bake(yields 12 to 14 servings)
directions: Melt margarine over medium-high heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth and thickened. Add onion, dry mustard, soy sauce and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.

title: v-8 soup
directions: *Green beans, zucchini, corn, peas, celery, carrots, potatoes, broccoli, cabbage.

title: beef and cheese macaroni
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine; add dried beef pieces. Fry about 2 minutes on medium heat.
Add milk and cheese cubes. Cook and stir over medium heat until it thickens somewhat.
Pour over cooked macaroni; mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with margarine.
Add half of stuffing mix. Place chicken on top of stuffing.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add chopped onion.
Cover with remaining 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Add margarine and pour chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Bring cherry juice to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add Coke and chill until it can be beaten.
Cut cherries.
Add cherries, pineapple and pecans to jello mixture.
Stir together and refrigerate until jelled.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: baby food cake
directions: Pour everything together in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into a prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done and cool.
Boil spaghetti until done. In skillet, saute bell pepper, onion and mushrooms; stir in both soups, tomatoes with juice and chopped Velveeta.
Let simmer and turn skillet off while you debone chicken.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces and stir in sauce.
Mix cooked spaghetti with sauce. Use 1 cup of chicken broth in mixture if needed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger and bean pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain grease.
Add green beans, mashed potatoes and tomato soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together and pour in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: best vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, milk and sugar in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir salt and remaining ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon ice cream freezer, hand turned or electric.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour before serving.
Yield about 3 quarts and will serve 6.

title: calico chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add tomatoes, chicken and noodles.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes; top with almonds.
Bake for 10 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: save-a-penny casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in soup, spaghetti and vegetables. Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: spinach soup
directions: Mix ingredients except croutons and paprika.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until flavors are blended. Garnish with croutons or paprika, if desired.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions in margarine about 2 minutes.
Add green pepper and beef.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well, breaking up tomatoes.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch strips.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In large skillet, brown strips of meat in 1/4 cup hot oil.
Drain can of tomatoes, reusing liquid.
Add liquid, water, onions, garlic and gravy to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (1 1/4 hours).
Stir often.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Cut peppers into strips and add to meat. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add drained tomatoes (cut up). Cook 5 minutes more and serve over hot cooked rice.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls out flat on a large cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix with a beater mayonnaise, cheese and Ranch dressing.
Beat well.
Spread over baked crescent rolls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown your hamburger with chopped onion until just done. Drain well.
Now add all the other ingredients and simmer slowly for 2 or 3 hours, stirring often.

title: scotcherteen bars
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter in a saucepan. Bring to a boil (a full rolling boil), stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except marshmallows.
Beat well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Spread in well buttered 12 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate.
Cut into bars.
Yields 40 bars.

title: *beef-potato-yogurt stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in the oil very lightly, keeping the lid on the skillet.
Add meat and brown, breaking it into chunks.
Add beef stock or bouillon, potatoes and seasoning.
Simmer gently for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are soft.
Add yogurt.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: candy peanuts
directions: Put peanuts, sugar and water in saucepan. Cook until all the water is cooked out, stirring constantly.
Dump into pan and roast in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients above approximately 7 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: easy strawberry mousse
directions: Whir all ingredients in blender and chill.

title: sweet nuts
directions: Mix together and boil for 15 minutes, keep stirring,
Spread on cookie sheets, salt.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Mix. Turn off oven and let set for 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Shortly before guests arrive, place ice cream and sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour liquids on top.
Enjoy!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, seasoned salt and sugar; mix well.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sangria punch(nonalcoholic)
directions: Float lemon, orange and apple slices in punch and serve. Great with tacos.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Method 1:
Divide butter into 3 portions.
Place egg yolks with 1/3 of the butter in top of double boiler.
Keep water hot but not boiling.
Stir eggs and butter constantly.
When butter melts, add another portion and as it melts and the mixture begins to thicken, add remaining butter.
Keep stirring constantly.
As soon as mixture is thick, remove from heat and add seasonings.
The sauce is delicious served with vegetables.
Should sauce separate, beat 2 tablespoons boiling water, drop by drop.
Makes 1 cup sauce. Increase lemon juice to 1 1/2 tablespoons.

title: rice with onion and bay leaf
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine; add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until onion is wilted.
Add rice and stir to coat grains.
Add broth and bay leaf.
Bring to boil and cover.
Cook exactly 17 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and stir in remaining 1 tablespoon margarine.
Serves 6.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in 6 quarts boiling water until tender (15 minutes).
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Cook potatoes, drain and mash.
Add cheese to hot mashed potatoes and season with salt and pepper.

title: lemon-pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: bow knots
directions: In a bowl, add salt to egg yolks.
Beat until lemon color.
Add sugar and liquor.
Add sour cream and alternate with flour; mix well after each addition.
Knead on breadboard.
When you hear a crackling noise, keep kneading until shiny, blisters pop up and the dough doesn't stick anymore.
Make into 3 balls.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut center and twist.
Fry on hot frying pan. Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: superb baked fish
directions: Place fish in greased baking dish and saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender, about 7 minutes.
Blend in flour; add milk, stirring with whisk constantly.
After it thickens add cream and seasonings.
Bring to boiling point and pour over fish. Cover and bake in preheated 400°
oven about 15 minutes.

title: bronco buster salad
directions: Mix broccoli bunch, onion and raisins together.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over broccoli mixture and mix well. Refrigerate.
Can be made the night before.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Boil chicken 15 to 20 minutes.
Place in shallow pan.
Smash lemon by rolling on counter; this smashes juice before cutting. Cut open and spread juice over chicken.
You can scoop some lemon out of peel for extra zip!
Smash garlic and smear over chicken. Let chicken set 15 minutes or longer.

title: lemon angel fluff(low-cal)
directions: Break angel food cake in bite size pieces.
Mix pudding following directions.
Use second box if you like a thicker layer. Put crumbled cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan carefully.
Cover all over with pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 2 1/2 hours. Slice like a cake.

title: mom hjelden's pancakes
directions: Add water to dry ingredients to texture desired.
Cook as usual.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and beat until fluffy. Add cooled melted chocolate, then sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Add oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets; press a pecan half on top of each.
Bake at 375°. Don't brown.

title: granola
directions: Mix sugar, oil and honey in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Combine with all other ingredients except raisins; mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients and add to chicken while on the grill.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Blend together ground round, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and eggs and form into meatballs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs and cook uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in an 8 x 10-inch greased pan (until lightly browned).
Enjoy!

title: plain cake from scratch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or two layer cake pans.
This is a good cake and easy to eat.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Over very low heat
or	in a double boiler heat milk to 180°, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from heat.
Cover and let set at room
temperature until cooled to 110°.
This will take about 30 minutes,
depending
on room temperature.
Meanwhile wash pint jars and
lids
and
rinse well with very hot water. With whisk, stir
yogurt
into	hot milk, blending well.
Pour into jars and screw
lids
on
tightly.
Place
jars in small cooler and wrap a blanket
around
cooler
and
set in a warm place at least	3 hours, but not longer than overnight.
Will keep for 2 to 6 weeks. Keep refrigerated.

title: pork che shui
directions: Blend together	the
sherry, soy sauce, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Marinate
pork
tenderloins for at least 3 hours or overnight.	Bake
at
300°	for
1	1/2 hours.
Baste every 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix everything, except chicken, Doritos and cheese.
In casserole, put layers of Doritos, soups, chicken and Doritos. Then on top, cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream together 1 cup sugar, butter, Bisquick and milk.
Put in oblong greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Pour fruit over batter. Add 1 1/2 cups sugar over top and pour boiling water over top. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with cream.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Add 4 cups flour.
Add oil, sugar, salt, yeast and one of the last ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes by hand.
Cover with a cloth until double in size or about 1 hour. Punch down.
Make in rolls or bake in 2 loaf pans for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix and spread in a 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, margarine, flour, milk, vanilla and coconut. Pour into two ungreased pans. Cook 35 minutes at 350°. Makes its own crust.

title: chili sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add the rest of ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until thick.
Serve with hot dogs.

title: hot rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; add sugar, salt and shortening to the scalded milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Add about 2 cups of the flour to milk mixture.
Beat thoroughly and then add the softened yeast and beaten eggs.
Add more flour to make a soft dough (approximately 3 1/2 cups).
Turn onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in a lightly greased bowl and brush the top of the dough with shortening.
Dough may now be placed in refrigerator and stored for future use or let it rise until doubled in bulk.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together. Add eggs and vanilla.
Slowly blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Smooth out mixture until evenly spread.
Spread cherries on top, cover with pie lid.
Let it chill in refrigerator for two hours.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix hot water with soda.
Add alternately with flour, cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place 8 slices of bread in a large, well buttered glass pan. Top with ham, then cheese, then 8 more slices of bread.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings, beating in one egg at a time.
Pour over the bread, ham and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter and toss with corn flakes. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable dill dip(serves 50)
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well and place in sealed container in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Dip will last 6 months in refrigerator.
Good for all cold and hot vegetables.

title: frito dip
directions: Heat can of mushroom soup and add cheese and chilies.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water. Chill in the refrigerator until the mixture begins to get thick. Add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Make cake like it says on box.
Then after cake is done, let it cool.
Poke holes 1 inch apart in cake with wooden spoon.
Then take strawberries and puree in blender.
Pour strawberries on top of cake.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: To the grated sweet potatoes, add other ingredients; mix well. Bake 45 minutes at 325° in a Pyrex casserole dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll into a ball and refrigerate.
Cover with Saran Wrap. Keeps real good.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add dressing.
If you double this recipe, you can serve 30 to 40 people.

title: frozen viennese coffee pie
directions: Soften vanilla yogurt to spreading consistency. Spread in an even layer on bottom of crumb crust.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons of the chocolate sauce.
Place in freezer.
Chill 1 hour or until firm.
Soften coffee yogurt to spreading consistency. Spread in an even layer over vanilla yogurt. Drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon sauce in a lace pattern. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix and bake for 20-30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Do not cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: walt's punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice in punch bowl.
Blend apple juice into cranberry juice.
Take one 6-pack of 7-Up and blend into mixture. Use other 6-pack to make ice cubes (2 trays).
Chill punch.
Add ice cubes to punch mixture.
Enjoy.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, 2 cups warm water, salt and softened yeast.
Add flour; mix well.
Place in a large greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; refrigerate dough.
When ready to use, shape rolls and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise about 3 hours; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 5 dozen rolls.

title: cream tacos
directions: Mix beans and chili in large pot.
Add meat mix and cheese. Stir often so it won't stick.
When cheese is melted and mixed in good, add whipping cream (unwhipped).
Simmer until hot and bubbly, stirring frequently.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple burritos
directions: Roll 1 tablespoon of filling in each tortilla.
Put in baking dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients in heavy pan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: frosted orange creme drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend well and serve at once.
Garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.
Makes 3 cups or 2 servings.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain grease well.
Mix with hamburger, taco sauce, cheese and refried beans.
Mix on low heat until the cheese is melted.
Serve now with chips or keep warm in the crock-pot.

title: feta salad dressing
directions: To roast bell pepper, char over open flame until all sides are blackened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Place in a bowl, cover and let steam until cooled.
Peel, cut off top and discard seeds.
Chop to measure 1 tablespoon and reserve the remaining bell pepper for some other use.

title: cherry chocolate nut bars
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1 jelly roll pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips, cherries and nuts. Blend at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes. Stir in chocolate chips, cherries and nuts.
Spread in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar and Karo; bring to a boil.
Let boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix with popped corn.
Put in oven and bake 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hostess ham
directions: Pat brown
sugar
on
top of ham.
Pour Pepsi over ham. Attach pineapple
slices
with
toothpicks on sides and top of ham.
Wrap in tinfoil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: celery stuffed with shrimp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stuff celery with shrimp mixture.
Cut celery into 1/2-inch slices and serve with wooden picks as an hors d'oeuvre.
Makes a great dip, too.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in greased/floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream praline
directions: Mix cream with sugar and egg yolks; stir while cooking. Remove from heat before mixture
boils,
and
cool.
Then
add praline paste, previously prepared
by cooking together to the caramel point equal quantities of
almond nuts and sugar which are
cooled and reduced to
paste.
Strain
the
mixture;
add whipped cream and set in a
paper collared mold and freeze for 1 1/2 hours. Remove paper and serve.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add diced onions, if desired.

title: shoyu pork
directions: Use
empty
tomato sauce can for measuring water, sugar and shoyu.
Boil together all ingredients.
Simmer until done, about 1 hour.

title: seafood hot sauce
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
May freeze remaining sauce.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all ingredients in large skillet and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour mixture into long casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread according to directions on package.
Pour over bean mixture.
Bake until cornbread is done.

title: homemade beef stick(venison can be used)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly in a glass bowl; cover with Saran
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next day,
again mix thoroughly	and
refrigerate
overnight.
Repeat
for the third day.
On the fourth day, form into 5 logs, approximately 1 1/2
to 2	inches	diameter.
Bake on broiler pan in top of oven for
8 hours
at 200° turning every 2 hours.
When done, the log
looks pink but not raw when you slice into it.
Cool thoroughly.	This freezes well and is much better than locally purchased
beef logs.
If
you
have
trouble
finding Morton Tender
Quick
meat cure,
write Morton Salt, P.O. 355, Argo, Illinois 60501.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cover bottom of 10 or 12-inch frying pan with vegetable oil. Mix all ingredients and cook until cabbage is hot and starts to wilt.

title: overnight sweet rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and place the rolls in the pan.
Mix the white sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle this over the rolls. Sprinkle them with dry pudding and pour margarine on top.
Top with brown sugar and nuts and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together; add eggs and other ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan, greased.
Cook at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix, put into pints and freeze.
When ready to use, add one pint of frozen juice to 1 quart of 7-Up, Sprite or ginger ale.

title: sour cream sugared nuts
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Heat to 223°, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until nuts are well coated.
Spread on tray; separate nuts.
Cool thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
May be stored 3 to 4 months.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook in salted water 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash eggplant and add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.
I add 1/2 cup of cheese on top.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup of evaporated milk in double boiler, over hot water and stir until melted.
Can be done in microwave in dish.
Combine cake mix, remaining milk and oleo. Blend until mixture holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Pour melted caramels evenly on top.
Crumble remaining mix over caramels and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, cut in bars.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box.
When pudding comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Add chocolate cake mix; mix by hand.
Put mixture in 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let cool.
Best when served with Cool Whip as a topping.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 12 servings.

title: wiles family fudge
directions: Melt on very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Pour into buttered pie plate and refrigerate.

title: pasta friatta
directions: Mix Mozzarella and Colby. Saute onion. Add ham and garlic. Combine eggs, parsley and cheeses. Add pasta. Combine with onion, ham, garlic mixture. Cook on top of stove in greased skillet for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix until smooth and stir in small can of crab.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to season.
Serve with carrot sticks, crackers and chips.

title: california pie(serves 8)
directions: Saute green peppers in margarine until crisp.
Add soup; stir in milk.
Add onion, potatoes and carrots.
Heat to a boil.
Add tuna, heat again.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Place unrolled rolls on top as a crust topping.
Sprinkle cheese on dough.
Bake 14 minutes or until medium brown at 400°.

title: banana orange surprise
directions: In a big bowl, place sliced bananas.
Add drained mandarin oranges.
Mix together in another bowl the other ingredients. Pour over bananas and oranges.
Mix and chill several hours.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil to make a roux.
Add flour when vegetables are done.
Peel shrimp.
Boil shells in water to make fish stock.
Remove shells from water.
Add shrimp stock to sauteed vegetables.
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: aunt grace's gingerbread
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Mix with electric mixer cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, sugar, oil, molasses and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternating with the buttermilk.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans (not loaf type).
Bake at 350° to 375° until done. Tester will come out clean.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes, in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Potatoes to be added during the last 45 minutes of the baking process.
Serves 4.

title: quick start breakfast drink
directions: In mixer bowl beat 2 eggs well add 2 cups sour milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly then add 1/4 cup melted shortening and mix well.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pam your pan.
Combine all ingredients, pour into pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients in food processor.
Refrigerate ball of dough overnight.
Pinch off quarter-size balls of dough and press with thumb onto cookie sheet.
Add 1/2 pecan on top, if desired.
Bake at 325°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southwest stew
directions: In skillet brown beef and onions.
Drain any excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good served with cornbread.

title: linguine with cauliflower
directions: Parboil cauliflower; drain and set aside.
Do not discard water.
In separate pan, saute onion.
Add anchovies.
Cook until anchovies melt.
Add raisins, nuts, cooked cauliflower, saffron and just enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes (use water that cauliflower was cooked in).
Mix cauliflower with linguine.
Add Romano cheese.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, ending with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yields about 1 cup.

title: apple betty
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread, in a 1-quart baking dish.
Top with bread cubes; drizzle with honey.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve warm, topped with cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut marshmallow bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugars with butter and peanut butter.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Press into bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of an ungreased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over crust.
Use wet knife to spread evenly to 1/2-inch from side of pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and peanuts over Marshmallow Creme.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer a large Pyrex dish with lettuce.
Sprinkle frozen green peas.
Add a layer of onion.
Add water chestnuts.
Layer with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add bacon bits.

title: lela's canadian goodies
directions: Cream powdered sugar and butter or oleo thoroughly.
Add egg; mix well.

Add vanilla, chopped nuts and chopped dates; mix well. Then roll into small balls and roll them in finely chopped coconut. Bake on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet 12 minutes at 375°. Watch closely the last 2 or 3 minutes as coconut browns fast and might burn.

title: sausage and pepperoni pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble sausage into medium skillet. Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove sausage and drain on paper towels.
In large lightly greased casserole dish, layer half of the noodles, half of the sausage and half of the remaining ingredients.
Repeat with second layer of noodles, then sausage and then remaining ingredients, reserving several pepperoni slices to garnish the top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine.
Add sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs, yeast, and flour to cooled mixture: mix well.
Store in slightly oiled Tupperware container overnight in refrigerator.
Tupperware should be large because dough will expand.
Make into rolls 2 hours before serving.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in buns.
Wrap in foil.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chutney glazed cheese pate
directions: Blend the cream cheese with shredded cheese until well mixed. Mix the sherry, curry powder and salt until blended.
Shape into a cake about 5 inches in diameter onto serving plate.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour or as long as overnight.
Before serving, pile mango chutney and green onions on top.
Surround with crisp sesame or whole wheat wafers or crackers.
Also good with celery and zucchini sticks and sliced cucumbers.

title: chocolate-cherry thumbprints
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1
cup morsels,
melted;	mix
well.
Stir in oats, flour and baking powder;
mix
well.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour. Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press deep centers with thumb.
Place one
cherry into each center.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Drizzle remaining 1 cup melted chocolate chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid to the drained pineapple juice.
Boil juice and water; add 1 box of Jell-O.
Stir in cranberry sauce until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable scallop
directions: In 1 1/2-quart square casserole, layer half of the zucchini, onion, tomatoes, chilies and croutons, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add cheese and cook 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Tear lettuce into bowl.
Add drained kidney beans, chopped onion, grated Cheddar cheese, chopped tomato and crushed tortilla chips. Add ground beef. Toss together.
Toss with the bottle of Catalina dressing.
Serves large gathering.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Brown bacon and saute onions in drippings.
Add tomato sauce and mix well.
Season to taste.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are red.
Set aside.
Cook rice and add to shrimp mixture.
Serves six.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Chicken broth may be used instead of water to cook rice in.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil the grated zucchini until tender.
Drain well.
To the zucchini, add the sugar, lemon juice, crushed pineapple and juice. Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 6 minutes.
Remove form heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Pour in hot jars.
Cover and let set in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, flour and salt together.
Place margarine on top of rhubarb mixture.
Place mixture in a 9-inch double pie crust (glass pie pan).
Bake 10 minutes uncovered in microwave on High setting, then 10 to 15 minutes in regular oven set at 400°.
Crust will be browned when done.
Cool on pie rack.

title: 24 hour sweet pickles
directions: Cut pickles lengthwise.
Pack jars with onion and dill.
Bring the vinegar, water, salt and sugar to a boil and pour over pickles.
Seal.
Put in oven and bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: onion pie
directions: Line an 8-inch pie pan with pastry.
Sprinkle the flour over the pastry.
Fill the pan with sliced onions, dot with butter. Add salt and pepper and pour the sweet cream over all.
Top with pastry.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pepperoni-cheese spread
directions: Chop pepperoni (use food processor); mix with cream cheese and parsley. In separate bowl, whip the whipping cream. Fold into pepperoni mixture (using a mixer at this point works fine). Put in bowl (it helps for unmolding to spray bowl with Pam) and chill.

title: baked spinach
directions: Heat spinach until thawed; drain and cool.
Beat eggs with mixer; add spinach, melted butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Add all cheeses; fold until well blended.
Pour in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add whipped cream and vanilla.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill until ready to serve, then add chilled pie filling.
I make this in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour, pinch of salt (more to taste), pinch of pepper, and dry mustard.
Add milk with 2 shakes of tabasco sauce.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Arrange layer of asparagus in bottom of buttered dish and cover with grated cheese.
Pour half of white sauce over asparagus, add another layer of asparagus, then rest of cream sauce.
Top with grated cheese and garnish with almonds.
Arrange as daisies, grated cheese for centers.
Pour in 2 quart baking dish and heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: fish amandine
directions: Combine flour, seasoned salt and paprika.
Roll fish in flour mixture and place in single layer in a well-greased baking dish. Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over portions.
Broil about 4 inches from heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Let soften, about 5 minutes.
Place saucepan over low heat, cook 5 minutes, stirring, until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Cool slightly.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cups of crumb mixture. Press remainder into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Combine cream cheese and milk; mix until well blended. Add remaining sugar (1/4 cup), egg and vanilla. Mix well. Pour in 9 x 13 pan over crumb crust. Top with chopped apples. Sprinkle with 2 cups of reserved crumb mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve chilled or serve warm topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: basic fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in fridge.
Add 1 quart of ice cubes or sherbet.

title: sour cream chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in the 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Combine onion mixture in a bowl with chopped chicken and green chili peppers; set aside.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion. Blend salad dressing, sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables and toss. Top with green pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and 1/2 bottle of cherry juice. Add drained pineapple, fruit cocktail, chopped cherries and 1 cup of nuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.

title: rice stuffed avocados
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in medium saucepan.
Add rice and cook until rice is golden, stirring.
Add onion and celery and continue to cook gently for 3 minutes, stirring.
Add chicken stock and salt; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Remove from heat.
Stir egg, cheese and Worcestershire sauce together and mix into rice along with parsley.
Heat oven to 350°. Cut avocados in half; remove stones and put avocado halves in a shallow baking pan.
Add 1/4 inch hot water to pan.
Spoon rice mixture into hollows in avocados.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until crumbs are browned and avocados are hot.

title: christmas salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Make lime jello as directed and set until firm.

title: carrot salad with raisins, nuts & sour cream
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except carrots.
Place carrots on ice for 1 hour.
Grate them coarsely into a bowl.
Add and mix lightly.
Place the salad in
a
bowl.
Pour
over it 1 cup or more sour cream.
Toss the salad if you wish.

title: tarall(italian sugar cookies)
directions: Blend butter and oil together.
Add sugar and cream well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into batter. Pinch off small pieces; roll and form into knots and braids.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, parsley flakes, basil, salt and canned tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together; add other ingredients and put in pie crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. You may serve with a glob of Cool Whip, if you like.

title: real chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper until done.
Save broth.
Debone chicken.
Cut potatoes, carrots and celery in broth to cook (keep broth).
Take out vegetables and keep 3 cups broth.
Combine chicken and vegetables including peas.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then the dry ingredients.
Make small balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour; beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: terry brock's strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together well.
Chill.
Serve with cut fruit.

title: layer salad
directions: In a dish, in the bottom of dish, place lettuce.
Over lettuce, spread peas.
Over peas, sprinkle crushed bacon.
Over crushed bacon, place sliced eggs.
Continue layering these ingredients. Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
(Use mixer.)
Spread over top of layered salad.
Top with bacon and eggs and sprinkle with cheese.

title: four bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Put bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: blue cheese bites
directions: Cut one (8 ounce) package refrigerated biscuits in quarters. Arrange in two 8-inch round baking dishes.
Melt together 1/4 cup butter and cheese.
Put mixture over biscuit pieces, coating well. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve hot. Makes 40.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except apples, together until smooth. Have apples sliced and peeled in a dish.
Combine 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 10-inch pan that is greased and floured.
Put sliced apples around, then sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pour rest of batter.
Make another layer of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sherry zucchini cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat together oil, sugar and eggs. Stir in flour mixture.
Add zucchini and flavorings.
Add pineapple and lemon peel (nuts).
Turn into well-greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Dust top of cake with confectioners sugar.

title: crab casserole dip
directions: Mix well all but crab meat and cheese.
Fold in crab meat. Place in 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Place on warming tray while serving. Serve with crackers.
Serves 25.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Mommy cooks meat; puts noodles on with butter and mixs it.
I like fruit with it, too.

title: four cheese vegetable lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Coat Dutch oven or electric frypan with no fat cooking spray. Saute over medium heat for 7 minutes:
vegetable oil, broccoli, carrots, green onion and garlic powder.
In saucepan, bring flour and milk to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in spinach; reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Swiss cheese.
In greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spread 1/2 cup spinach mixture, 4 cooked lasagna noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 vegetable mixture and 1/2 spinach mixture.
Repeat, ending with noodles.
Spread reserved 1/2 cup spinach mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: 3 bean freyfurter casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, nuts, raisins and dates with 1 cup of flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour alternately with pineapple and applesauce.
Add soda and water.
Add floured nuts, etc.
Bake in tube pan at 325° until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put steak and mushrooms in heavy skillet; add onion and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring, 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 can beef broth and ketchup.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or until meat is tender.
Mix flour with remaining broth.
May add salt, pepper or other spice.
Slowly stir flour mixture into meat; cook until thick.
Remove.
Add sour cream; serve over rice or broad noodles or toast.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, eggs and oil.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in tube pan.

title: tuna-stuffed peppers
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add crumbled bread and toast, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Add all ingredients, except whole peppers.
Heat to blend flavors.
Fill prepared peppers and place in suitable baking dish containing an inch of more of water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(These may also be cooked in a deep skillet, using 1 to 2 inches of water and place over low/medium heat for 25 minutes.)

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Grease skillet and sprinkle with corn meal. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes and half of the flour in a bowl.
Work in more flour with hands until firm dough forms.
Roll out on floured board to a circle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into triangles or circles. Cook in lightly greased griddle or skillet until brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.

title: peach pudding salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until dissolved. At this point, I add diced peaches and peach juice; chill in 9 x 13-inch dish to serve as salad.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies; my favorite recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.

title: clam chowder
directions: *Be sure you have New England clam chowder, not Manhattan style.

title: frozen hot chocolate
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir enough milk in to form a smooth paste.
Then stir in all but 2 tablespoons remaining milk.
Stir over low heat until mixture is warm and sugar is dissolved.
Pour into a shallow pan or ice cube trays.
Cover well and freeze for at least 6 hours.
Place chunks into a food processor bowl fitted with a steel blade.
Process with remaining 2 tablespoons milk until no lumps remain and mixture is thick and light in color.
Serve at once in frosted goblets as spoon drink or scrape into a bowl with cover and refrigerate overnight.
Scoop out and serve frozen.
Yields 6 to 7 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion, 1 teaspoon cumin and salt.
(Drain off any grease.)
In saucepan, mix 1 (15 ounce can) tomato sauce, 1/4 teaspoon cumin and hot sauce, as desired. (Simmer as you fix other things.)
Chop green onions and 3 cups grated Cheddar cheese and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Remove from heat. Let chicken cool.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes until brown.

title: grilled ham steak
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the preserves, mustard, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly combined, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple slices and chicken in large frying pan. Add chicken, laying pineapple slices on top. Pour juice from pineapple into sauce and cover. Cook over low heat until thoroughly done.

title: french crepes
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and sift again.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and shortening.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Pour enough batter onto a hot greased griddle to make one pancake, about 4 to 5-inches in diameter.
Tip pan to make the pancake as thin as possible.
Bake until browned, turning to brown on both sides.
Keep hot until all cakes are baked.
Spread with jelly. Roll and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in heavy pot then remove to drain on paper towel.
Saute onion, celery, pepper and garlic until tender. Remove from pot.
Add shortening and when it gets hot, add rice and brown lightly.
Add crawfish and cook 3 minutes.
Add sausage, vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: amish dark chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
margarine.
Add
cocoa
and mix well. Add eggs.
Mix in flour and milk alternately, then add boiling water. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach until almost done.
Drain and mix with sour cream and soup mix.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
The last 5 minutes add a can of French fried onion rings for topping.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Cut in half and boil as many peppers as you want for 1 meal for 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain.
Season instant potatoes with oleo, salt, sour cream and chives.
Put in peppers.
Bake for a few minutes and sprinkle with paprika.
Cheese could be used.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of oil until white.
Remove and drain.
Add mushrooms and onions and saute until just barely soft. Add frozen veggies and cook until soft, not mushy.
Add chicken and remove from stove.
Cool.

title: pumpkin pie (diabetic)
directions: Place pudding in saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cool, stir and add pumpkin, spices and sugar twin.
Mix well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except popcorn and soda.
Boil 5 minutes. Do not stir.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn which should be in a large roasting pan greased with butter.
Stir until popcorn is well covered.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice the apples; cube enough bread to cover apples.
Beat together the egg, melted margarine, sugar, flour and spices.
Pour over cubed bread and apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco and blend well (like fine meal).
Add buttermilk; mix. Roll out and cut.
Place biscuits on a greased pan and bake until brown.
Goes with everything!

title: herb biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Melt butter in oblong dish.
Put other ingredients in and then add biscuits and turn them to coat. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lo-cal quiche
directions: Beat the eggs slightly.
Add the milk and seasonings.
Mix. Stir in the cheese.
Pour the mixture into a pie size pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm in the center.
Cool. Slice and serve warm or cool; 200 calories per serving.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine egg, sugar and 3 cups of 1/2 gallon of milk.
Cook on top of stove until mixture reaches 160° or until it coats a metal spoon.
After this cools, add remaining milk, condensed milk, vanilla, food coloring and peaches.
Mix and freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: pinch me cake(makes a great breakfast or brunch dessert)
directions: Make a mixture of cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in a plastic bag. Quarter each biscuit into 4 sections and roll each into a small round ball with hands.
Shake biscuits into cinnamon and sugar mix, coating well.
Grease a tube pan.
Make a syrup of oleo, 1 1/4 cups sugar and vanilla in a pan and heat until sugar dissolves.
Layer in tube pan the pecans and biscuits and cover layers with the syrup.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.
Do not overcook.
Cool and remove from pan carefully and press any balls loose back into cake.
Form on a plate.
Better served warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add corn, milk and melted butter. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Check doneness by inserting knife blade, when blade comes out dry, pudding is done.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Add enough water to the first three ingredients to make 1 gallon.
Freeze several hours.
Before serving, remove punch from freezer, letting it get to a slushy stage.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to make 2 gallons of punch.

title: mom's chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken in water (enough water to completely cover chicken).
When chicken is cool, debone.
Add stuffing with seasonings to broth from chicken.
Gradually add the cornbread along with the deboned chicken.
Dressing should be slightly soupy.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Spread pecans on cookie sheet or shallow baking pan and pour the melted butter over the pecans, mixing well. Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in boiler and add the brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.

title: neptune skillet supper
directions: Measure 1 Tbsp. oil from top of artichoke marinade into skillet.
Add garlic and onion and cook until softened.
Add tomatoes and simmer three or four minutes.
Cut fish steaks in half to make four portions.
Add to skillet along with artichokes and the marinade.
Simmer until fish is cooked, spooning sauce over top once or twice, about ten minutes.

title: krunch bars
directions: In a large saucepan, melt together the butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Spread half of this mixture on the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13 pan and refrigerate.

Melt chocolate chips and add confectioners sugar and water until consistency is slightly thicker than frosting. Spread this mixture on top of the first mixture and place in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the Rice Krispies mixture, patting down.
Cut into squares.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook celery and onion in oil until wilted.
Add beef.
Cook until done.
Add sauce and crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: philbrook farm dark bread
directions: Measure into cup the graham flour and then turn into a large bowl.
Sift into the bowl over the graham flour the 2 cups flour, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Mix together lightly the molasses and buttermilk or sour milk and add to the flour mixture.
Mix and turn into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Turn out to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, a little at a time, while stirring.
Add 1 egg.
Set aside.
Sift flour and baking powder. Set aside.
Mash bananas with soda.
Add sour cream.
Add flour mixture alternately with banana-sour cream to shortening and sugar.
When all combined, add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix bacon, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over onion, broccoli and raisins.
Mix.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight, covered.

title: chicken dressing bake
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Make the stuffing according to directions.
Put a layer of dressing in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon the creamed chicken mixture on top.
Put the rest of the dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese and potato chips). Toss lightly and spoon into 1-quart casserole. Spread cheese and chips on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through and brown on top. Cut into squares and serve.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Pour into greased and floured oblong loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, cover with miniature marshmallows and let melt.
Ice in pan.

title: 3 day dill pickles
directions: You will also need 2-quart jars.
Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Put dill in jars and add pickles, alum and more dill on top of pickles (can add onion slices if desired).
Pour boiling hot liquid over pickles and seal jars.
Let set 1 week to 10 days before eating.

title: the best instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in very large bowl.
Store at room temperature in plastic containers or keeps forever in the freezer. Add 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes a ton, but great to give away!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a baking dish, making sure the cornstarch is not lumpy, then sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
I usually double this recipe.

title: potato cakes
directions: Peel potatoes and soak in water for several hours.
Grate with onion.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot well-greased skillet, in small cakes.
Turn and brown on both sides.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: garlic-lemon-mint vinegar
directions: Put into a bottle the cloves of garlic and mint sprigs.
Add lemon peel.
Fill with vinegar.

title: annie's crawfish fettucini
directions: Add onions and celery to melted butter in a large heavy sauce pan.
Saut for 10 minutes until onion is clear.
Add flour and mix well.
Cook until thickened.
Add parsley and crawfish.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cream, cheese, and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in cooked and drained noodles.
Pour into a buttered 3 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: party pecan balls
directions: Cream 1/4 cup of confectioners sugar and butter in mixing bowl until smooth. Add vanilla; blend well. Add flour and salt; blend well. Stir in pecans. Cover with aluminum foil. Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Thoroughly combine beef, milk, catsup, crumbs, onion, salt and oregano and pepper.
Spread in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Spread on meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Top with dill slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: unbelievable cookieswestboro, missouri
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by scant tsp. on a cookie sheet.
(Be careful not to make them too large or they will burn on the bottom before the top is done)
Bake till lightly browned on top at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayo, water chestnuts and green onions. Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
If desired, serve with pumpernickel bread or crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine until tender. Mix the remaining ingredients and spoon in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with pork or chicken.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Add onion, bouillon cubes, garlic powder, bay leaves, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken.
Remove skin and debone.
Return to broth and add beans, corn, cubed potatoes and mixed vegetables.
Simmer 1 hour or so. Serve over biscuits or make dumplings and drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth.

title: simplified quiche
directions: *Recipe found elsewhere in book (in Pastry section).

title: mallow whip sweet potatoes
directions: Mix first nine ingredients together and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Top with large marshmallows and maraschino cherries. Bake at 400° until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: hopple popple
directions: Peel and dice potato; mix with onion and fry in bacon drippings.
Add salt and pepper and cubed bread until grease is absorbed.
Beat egg and pour slowly into skillet until cooked. Serve vegetables and salad or as a breakfast with toast or biscuits.
Can add ham or bacon chunks.

title: oysters bienville
directions: Make sauce of butter, flour, garlic, onion juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed and liquid.
Add mushrooms, shrimp and sherry.
Slide oysters under broiler until edges just curl.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese, then cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cayenne-paprika mixture.
Slide back under broiler for 5 to 8 minutes until bubbly and slightly brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Combine sausage, rice and 1 1/2 c water in a medium sauce pan, Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add vegetables, red peppers and salsa. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes or longer if needed. Garnish with sliced green onions, if desired.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Reserve 5 tablespoons drippings.
Except bacon and Cheddar cheese, mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Mix in bacon drippings.
Pour into well-greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or when knife comes out clean.

title: oven chicken
directions: Wash, dry, salt and pepper chicken.
Put in baking dish. Combine soup mix, salad dressing and preserves.
Cover chicken with this sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour kebabs
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In saucepan mix brown sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly add juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
On toothpicks thread meat and pineapple.
Place on cookie sheet. Baste with sauce.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn once and baste with sauce.
Keep remaining sauce for dipping.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; save liquid.
Flake salmon.
Heat milk.
Add breadcrumbs and butter or margarine.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add salmon liquid and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, green pepper, onion, lemon juice, pepper and salmon; mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm in center from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen from sides of pan with a spatula and invert on a serving platter.
Serve plain or with a sauce.

title: oyster stew
directions: Wash oysters and remove any shell, drain.
Make a paste of margarine and flour in skillet over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper and milk, stirring constantly. Add oysters, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Cook until oysters are plump and their edges curl.
Do not boil.
Serve hot with oyster crackers.

title: "cheese ball"
directions: Beat cream cheese, shredded sharp Cheddar, margarine, garlic powder and ground red pepper until well blended.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers or Ritz chips.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-pimento cheese saladthis was lollie prafka's recipe
directions: Heat the pineapple and juice.
Then add pimento spread and jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Fold in cool whip and refrigerate until firm.

title: good things
directions: Divide crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Mix all remaining ingredients together, except egg white and sesame seed.
Spread on rolls.
Roll up lengthwise and cut into 8 pieces.
Brush top with egg white and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 18 minutes.
Yield: 32.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: In medium-sized skillet, over
medium heat, saute bacon until almost crisp; add onion, celery and mushrooms.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
In a large bowl, combine bacon mixture, wild rice, bread crumbs, sausage, oregano and sage. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's cutout cookies
directions: Heat milk and sugar together.
Stir in soda; mix.
Set aside and cool.
Put in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Then stir in milk; mix again.
Chill.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on bread board with flour.
Cut out cookies with cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: glorified graham cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and boil for 2 minutes.
Let cool. Add pecans and vanilla; stir.
Line crackers on cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil. Spoon glaze over crackers. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: touch of lemon sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, lemon peel, lemon juice and
vanilla.
Add	salt,
soda
and
cream of tartar to flour. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 2 minutes before removing from sheet.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Boil sugar and cream together until it forms a firm ball when tried in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla; cool and beat until creamy.
Add the chopped pecans and stir well.
Drop by tablespoons on buttered paper and allow to cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All and onion and pour in casserole dish. Mix soups; pour over chicken and vegetable mixture. Combine milk, mayonnaise and flour. Mix well and pour over casserole ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco well.
Mix in flour and milk. Add flavoring and eggs; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes without opening door.
Place a pan of water under cake to prevent dryness.

title: biltmore apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour and sugar, then add shortening, yeast and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Add more flour if needed.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 1 1/2 hours before baking, let stand at room temperature, then roll out.
Form rolls and let raise in warm place for 1 hour before baking.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: make a meal soup
directions: In Dutch oven sprayed with Pam, saute turkey and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip wafer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with foil, lightly grease foil.
Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl until light. Add egg; beat until creamy.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoons 3-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden and centers are set.
Cool completely on foil, then peel foil from cookies.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: punch
directions: Mix sherbet, lemonade and small amount of soda until soft.
Add remaining soda and stir good.
Makes 43 punch cups 3/4 full. Different flavors of sherbet may be used.

title: pasta-bean salad
directions: Combine macaroni, beans, peas and carrots in a large bowl; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, parsley, cheese, lemon juice, garlic and basil, mixing well.
Add to macaroni mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: sicilian steak sandwich
directions: Cook meat in margarine.
Cook green pepper in dressing 5 minutes.
Add onion and tomato; continue cooking for 5 additional minutes.
For each sandwich, place meat on the bottom half of the French bread loaf; cover with vegetables.
Top with a cheese slice and place under the broiler until the cheese melts just slightly.

title: chocolate-cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, cocoa, salt and only 1 cup of the flour.
Mix well.
Then stir in the remaining 1 1/4 cups flour and blend well, scraping down bowl.
Add the egg and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer or beat 300 strokes by hand.
Scrape down bowl.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Stir down, beating about 25 strokes.

title: waffles a la russe
directions: Prepare waffle mix as directed on package. Drop batter from a tablespoon onto a greased, heated waffle iron for small round waffles.
Be careful not to let waffles touch.
When done, put aside.
Just before serving, reheat in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Top each with sour cream and caviar.
Makes about 2 small waffles.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream together melted margarine, cocoa, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Add baking soda, flour and salt gradually; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallow cream evenly over top of cake.
Return to warm oven only long enough to melt marshmallows.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: sweet potato souffle with topping
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into buttered pan.

title: parm-a-loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except barbecue sauce; mix lightly.
In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread with barbecue sauce. Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with additional cheese.

title: corned beef casserole(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 2-quart round baking dish, layer corned beef, sauerkraut, dressing and cheese. Top with bread cubes.
Drizzle bread with butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Five minutes before cake is finished cooking, heat milk and sugar in a saucepan to a rolling boil. When cake is done, use a fork to make holes in cake.
Pour milk and sugar mixture over cake while hot.
Refrigerate.
When cake is cool, top with Cool Whip and cover with coconut.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in flour, coconut and pecans. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°. When done, spread marshmallow cream on hot cake. Cool before frosting.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey in a small bowl.
Add dry milk. Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll the balls in the graham cracker crumbs.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 treats.

title: carol's dump cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay in this order:
cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple (do not drain the juice), yellow cake mix (sprinkled evenly) and melted margarine poured on top of everything.
Put nuts on top.
Sprinkle coconut on top of everything.
Do not mix up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut.

title: michigan sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Add sugar if needed.

title: crawfish and corn soup
directions: Fry bacon to a crispy texture.
Remove and cool.
In drippings, saute onion, bell pepper, green onions and parsley. Put sauteed herbs into large Dutch oven or pot.
Saute crawfish. Add crawfish to onion mixture.
Empty canned items into pot.
Add whipping cream and stir.
Add milk or water until the soup is to your desired consistency (it should be pretty thick).
Crumble bacon into soup.
Cook over a medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or alone.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg
yolks to one can milk.
Add lemon juice.
Mix and pour
in baked pie shell.
Beat whites of eggs with sugar. Beat until
stiff.
Pour
over pie.
Bake in oven on slow heat until brown.

title: incredibly-rich-from-scratch new year's eggnog(mm-m-m!  with grandma's rich cream right from the cow!)
directions: Combine milk and 1 cup cream; scald.
Beat 1/3 cup sugar into beaten egg yolks.
Add salt and slowly stir in milk while beating. Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
(This custard can be made up, refrigerated and finished just before serving.)

title: cherry center balls
directions: Mix ingredients except crumbs, together until smooth with electric mixer.
Form ball and put cherry in center.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: oats crispies cookies
directions: Combine the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Add the remaining ingredients. Shape into a roll and wrap in waxed paper. Chill overnight. Cut into slices and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: bread or rice pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Add bread crumbs or rice and margarine.
Add sugar, salt and eggs. Stir slowly into hot milk mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the Miracle Whip with 1 cup of cold water and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: boiled oatmeal cocoa cookies
directions: Stir sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk, vanilla and butter. Heat at medium until it reaches full boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Add oats and peanut butter.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Drop quickly by spoon on waxed paper or pan.
Let stand until cool.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt together caramels, cream and vanilla.
Add pecans and mix.
Spoon out on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin.
Dip cooled candy in the chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.

title: easy roast with potatoes, carrots and gravy
directions: Place roast
in
roasting pan with tight fitting cover. Put potatoes
and
carrots around roast.
Sprinkle 1/2 package beefy onion soup	over the top.
Stir 2 tablespoons flour in 2 cups hot water
and	pour over all.	Cover with lid and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours
at
Chill
and slice roast thinly when cool.	Reheat and serve with rice, salad and bread of choice.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix avocado, black pepper, lemon juice and garlic salt and onion salt to taste.
Layer in order: Bean dip, avocado mix, sour cream, picante sauce and cheese.
Top with sliced black olives. Serve with nachos.

title: chocolate peanut candies
directions: Over double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening.
Cool slightly.
Blend peanut butter and butter thoroughly.
Add the peanuts, sugar and cereal.
Chill about 15 minutes.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls, using a fork, into chocolate.
Tap fork on side of bowl to allow excess chocolate to drip off.
Place on cookie sheet or flat tray and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Boil until about tender.
Drain.
Slice about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Fry in oil.
Turn and sprinkle with sugar and fry until glazed.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 11-inch dish at 350° until done.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and sausage in butter in a large Dutch oven for 5 minutes.
Add rice; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Add tomato juice, chicken broth, salt, savory and red pepper seasoning.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and ham; continue cooking for 15 minutes longer or until rice and shrimp are tender.
Stir in green onion.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add applesauce and soda. Add all dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Remove crusts from bread and line bottom and sides of casserole (cut bread in smaller pieces for sides).
Spread sausage over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage and cheese layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake 35 minutes.

title: homestyle chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican meatloaf
directions: Brown meat, add remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese and bring to a boil.
Place half of the mixture in baking dish.
Add tortillas and remaining meat.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If you want, you could add 1/2 cup of rice.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat
oven
Grease
and
flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan,
two 9-inch pans or three 8-inch round layer cake pans. Measure
all
ingredients
into
a	large
mixing bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3
minutes on	high
speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans. Bake
oblong cake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick
inserted in	center comes out clean.
Cool.	Frost with Vanilla Butter or Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to form dough.
If too stiff, soften with oil or Milnot.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruited sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and peaches, reserving 1/2 cup syrup from each. Place potatoes and peaches in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and reserved syrup. Stir until smooth. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Remove from heat and pour over potatoes and peaches. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: shrimp stuffer merlitons
directions: Cut merlitons in half and remove seed.
Parboil until fork-tender.
Scoop out meat and place shells on greased baking sheet.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage.
Melt cheese and Ro-Tel together.
Add sausage. Wash and chop broccoli.
Add raw if simmering for a long time in crock-pot or cook and then add.
Serve hot with nacho chips or Fritos.

title: lemon lush
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: mother's chocolate pound cake
