directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add other ingredients and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.
Bake in a tube pan.

title: hamburger-macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Brown beef and garlic in skillet, stirring with fork to break up meat.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add macaroni.
Mix again.
Pour into 1-quart casserole or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix melted oleo (butter) with bread crumbs and sprinkle over cheese. Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes until crumbs are toasty. Serves 4.

title: peppered beef tenderloin
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix smudge and rub on top of roast.
Place roast on rack in shallow roasting pan.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, onions and oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss to cover evenly.
Arrange potatoes around roast on rack.
Roast 55 to 65 minutes at 425°.
Let stand 15 minutes after removal.
Serve with salad, bread and other vegetable and fresh fruit.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix the 6 cups boiling water the the tea bags. Simmer the spices in 4 cups water about 10 minutes; drain.
Mix all together. Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, and spoon off fat.
Add next five ingredients, and simmer 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: apricot blush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve over crushed ice.
Garnish with orange, lemon and lime slices.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: In mixing bowl mix flour and sugar.
In saucepan melt margarine, cocoa and water.
Boil and pour over flour and sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix and pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until about 1/2 done.
Drain.
Add the other ingredients and mix well (except paprika).
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle paprika on top and return to oven for 10 more minutes to brown.

title: apple pudding
directions: Line the bottom of baking dish with apples, peeled and cut up. Mix all other ingredients to form a batter.
Pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in bottom of casserole (square).
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry.
Spread over chicken.
Mix bread crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine and cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until bubbling.

title: scripture bread(use k. j. v.)
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients until fluffy.
Add the third ingredient.
Sift the next 5 ingredients.
Add alternately with the 1/2 cup Judges 4:19.
Stir in 2 tablespoons Judges 14:18. Fold in the last 3 ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Cool 30 minutes.
Remove from pan to finish cooling.
Yields two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: deviled eggs-texas special
directions: Combine in order and chill.
Consistency is great.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread sausage in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, until slightly golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, baking powder and milk. Then add spices and salt.
Add flour.
They may need just a bit more flour (so dough looks dry).
Roll not too thin, about 1/4-inch, and cut with doughnut cutter.
Drop in hot oil and fry about 1 minute on 1 side, then flip and fry the other side.
Dip in xxxx sugar.
Very good.
Yields around 4 dozen.

title: turkey scallop
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add turkey and brown. Separately mix soup, milk and desired seasoning.
Put half the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add half the cooked turkey, then half the soup mixture.
Repeat the layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Uncover.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Simmer in 2 cups water until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Heat remaining liquids together and add sugar mixture.
Place in punch bowl or in crock-pot for serving.
Serves 50.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drop into medium hot deep fat fryer with teaspoon and finger.

title: grandmother's christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill overnight in a covered bowl.
Roll out in a log roll about the size of a lead pencil.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Store in an airtight container or Christmas can.
The longer they are stored, the better the flavor.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered cake pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Spoon into prepared pan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth. Spoon evenly over cake.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pintos
directions: Cook pintos in pan on low heat until beans are soft. Cut the onion and add to pintos. Cook until the onion is soft.
Add the Tabasco sauce.
Stir in.
Take off the stove and put pintos in refrigerator overnight.
Do not reheat. Eat cold.

title: spinach-sunflower salad
directions: Heat spinach over low heat or in oven until thawed.
Drain. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Toss with spinach. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with sunflower seeds.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze water out.

title: berry-cheese pie
directions: Mix cheese, 1 tablespoon sugar and lemon rind until blended. Spread over crust.
In saucepan, combine remaining sugar, cornstarch, strawberries and lemon juice.
Crush with masher. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring until thickened.
Let cool. Gently fold in blueberries with a spatula.
Spread over cheese in crust.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip on plate.
Spread remaining ingredients in order shown.
Use as dip with taco chips, Doritos, etc.

title: brie-fresh strawberry french toast
directions: Slice about 2/3 of the strawberries, reserving nice whole ones for garnish.
Spread 4 slices of bread with Brie cheese.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Cover each with a second slice of bread.

title: easy apple dessert *
directions: Crumble fig bars and mix with applesauce.
Add lemon rind, pour into greased dish or pan, sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, whip cream or milk.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the chicken, onion, celery, eggs and cracker crumbs.
Mix the mayonnaise, lemon juice, mushroom soup and pepper.
Mix 1/2 noodles in the chicken mixture and save the other half to sprinkle on top.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Wrap in aluminum foil for 15 minutes, then unwrap and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: breakfast in a glass
directions: Place all ingredients into blender and process until smooth. Chill before serving.

title: squash rolls
directions: Heat squash and milk in saucepan until bubbles form around edges.
Add oleo and stir.
Stir in sugar and salt.
In large bowl, mix 4 cups flour and yeast.
Stir in squash/milk mixture.
Add flour to make dough stiff enough to knead dough.
Knead 5 minutes until elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Bake and brush with butter.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes for bread or 15 to 20 minutes for rolls.

title: coca-cola ham
directions: Place ham in a deep pan.
Fill pan with enough Coca-Cola to cover about 3/4 of the ham.
Seal the pan with aluminum foil and bake at 275° all night or all day.
I bake mine from 11:00 PM until 9:00 AM.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring 6
cups of water to a boil.
Steep tea bags for 5 minutes.
Simmer
cloves, cinnamon, sugar and 1 quart of water in another
pot.
Remove tea bags, cloves and cinnamon sticks and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all and simmer.

title: wide eyed pizzas
directions: Measure 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, salt and crumbs.
Divide in 4 parts.
Make 4 1/2-inch circle and 1/2-inch thick.
Pinch edge of circle to stand up rim. Pour 2 tablespoons sauce in center.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle pizza with cheese.
Put in oven just long enough for the cheese to melt.

title: wine cellar's house mustard dressing
directions: Bring first 9 ingredients to a boil; mix well during the cooking.
Thicken with cornstarch and season with tarragon; return to a slow boil, then cool.
Whisk in vegetable oil and mayonnaise. At the Wine Cellar, a homemade mayonnaise is used, but Hellmann's can be substituted.
This makes enough for personal use and some for friends as gifts.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Strain punch, discarding spices.
Yields about 8 1/2 cups.

title: quick and easy chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased 12 x 14-inch pan.
Top with 1 package of Pepperidge Farm stuffing and drizzle 1/4 pound of melted butter over the top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Bake crust for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Sprinkle pie shell with sausage, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Beat eggs, cream and salt together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted on edge comes out clean.

title: new yorker cookies
directions: First Layer:
Put margarine (1/2 cup), white sugar and cocoa in heavy saucepan and heat slowly.
Stir until smooth.
Add beaten egg and vanilla and mix well.
Remove from heat.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan and put in refrigerator.

title: champagne
directions: Mix crumbs and butter to make crust.
Press into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix cream cheese and sugar in bowl.
Mix fruit with Cool Whip, mixing well.
Add to the cheese mixture.
Spread over the crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first five ingredients.
Place 1/2 the potatoes in 2-quart casserole dish and cover with 1/2 the onions and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mother's plain cake
directions: Pan:
Use a tube cake pan; line only the bottom of pan. Grease thoroughly the sides, bottom, paper and especially the funnel of pan.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Combine meat and oil in 3-quart glass casserole.
Cover and microwave on High setting for 10 minutes, stirring once.
Stir flour into meat.
Add remaining ingredients and then microwave on Low-defrost setting for 76 minutes.
Stir after 30 minutes.
If meat is not fork-tender, microwave on same setting for 19 minutes.

title: frozen grapes
directions: Wash and snip white seedless grapes into clusters.
Dip each cluster into slightly beaten egg white (add water to egg whites) and then into granulated sugar.
Place on tray covered with paper towel to crystallize.
May be made the day before and put in cool place, but do not refrigerate.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown hamburger and put in baking dish. Dice a layer of onion and then potatoes. Pour soup over the top and cover with milk. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: festive rice salad
directions: Mix all and chill before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, melt 1/2 stick butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix together and add juice from peas and asparagus.
Melt in cheese.
Layer peas, asparagus and almonds.
Top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stuff Pita Pocket Bread and serve.

title: swiss cheese and mushroom quiche
directions: Cover bottom of pie crust with grated Swiss cheese.
Chop onion and mushrooms; saute in butter with salt, pepper and thyme to taste.
Make a custard of eggs, milk, flour, salt and dry mustard.
Pour custard over mushroom layer; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until solid in center when jiggled.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Combine spinach, green onions, bacon bits, dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spread mixture over each tortilla and roll to enclose filling.
Moisten edge and seal. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch portions. Serve cold.

title: canned grape jelly made from frozen concentrate juice
directions: Stir sugar into water.
Place on high heat, stirring constantly; bring quickly to a full rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the pectin.
Add thawed concentrated grape juice and mix well. Pour immediately in hot containers (jelly jars) and seal.
Makes 8 to 9 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook package of frozen broccoli until it falls apart.
Drain.
Add celery soup and rice.
Mix and place in casserole dish with Cheez Whiz. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let chill for several hours before serving.
Great to use with all vegetables.

title: yeast rolls(use mixer with doughhooks)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat water to 120°.
Add sugar and yeast to heated water; set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour, dry milk, salt, oil, eggs (slightly beaten) and water mixture.
Knead on high until well blended.
Gradually add flour until it forms a nice stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Knead again with hands, about 2 minutes.
Roll out dough and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Cook for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 35 to 40.

title: french bread sandwich
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise.
Put halves of bread on lined cookie sheet.
Spread on Cheez Whiz; add ketchup, soup and soup mix to browned and drained hamburger meat.
Mix thoroughly and spoon onto bread, spreading to edges, not piling high.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: flemish pork chops
directions: Brown chops in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place in 2-quart casserole with lid.
Add onion slices to skillet in which chops were browned and cook until transparent.
Add wine and stock; cook 1 minute.
Pour the liquid and onions over chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix together and fold in broccoli.
Top with crushed Cheese Nips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
If you double recipe, bake 45 minutes.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Brown onion and sausage in oil. Add tomatoes and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes. Add garlic, carrots, potatoes and cabbage. Cover with stock and simmer 10 minutes. Add meat, salt, pepper and paprika to taste. Cover and simmer 1 to 3 hours. Add more beef stock if needed. This is a nice, spicy soup.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Cook onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is yellow; set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter, stir in flour and add milk.
Cook and stir until sauce boils.
Add salt and pepper.

title: seduction chicken(chicken marengo)
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken; drain most of oil.
Add the flour; cook over moderate heat until flour browns.
Gradually whisk in wine and water or chicken broth slowly to avoid lumping. Add tomato paste, thyme and garlic.
Put chicken back into pot when juices have drained from heat.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour for whole chicken and 30 minutes for cut up chicken.
Sliced mushrooms sauteed in olive oil can be added a few minutes before chicken is done.
Chopped Italian parsley is also a nice addition.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Sift powder sugar.
Add cream cheese; mixing well.
Fold in peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: vegetable dill dip(easy and good)
directions: Mix all together and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Spread pineapple over cake when cake is cool.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk; set aside.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk, then add to cream cheese mixture.
Spread over pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add water to get the thickness you want. Simmer 45 minutes. You may add chili powder.

title: picante sauce
directions: Stir and blend ingredients.
Simmer on low heat 30 minutes stirring frequently.
Pour in prepared jars and process in boiling water bath 30 minutes.

title: quick fudge
directions: Put everything in top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Spread on unbuttered pan and cool. Add 1 can marshmallow cream and add about 2 tablespoons peanut butter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, mix in sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Add melted butter.
Place pecans in the bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Add filling and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt together. Cut in Crisco.
Beat sugar, milk and egg and add to flour mixture. Knead briefly, roll out and cut biscuits.
Freeze.
Bake frozen. Do not thaw.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Can bake 2 or 3 or all.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juices.
Mix juices with pudding and tapioca pudding and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it bubbles.
Cool and add fruit.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes once.
Bake potatoes in microwave oven on High for 8 minutes.
Turn over; bake for 8 minutes longer.
Slice hot potatoes lengthwise; scoop out insides, saving shell.
Whip potatoes, margarine, cheese, onion, salt and pepper together; blend in milk gradually.
Spoon potato mixture back into shells; return to oven.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg and then bran.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine water and bananas.
Add alternately with sifted dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in waxed paper-lined loaf pan (5 x 9-inch) at 350° for
1 hour.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Let cool. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs. Combine with date mixture and beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat well and pour into oiled Bundt pan.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain well.
Cool.
Add vegetables and eggs.
Stir in salad dressing, salt and pepper. Chill.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and oil; blend in egg, vanilla and sour milk. In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to moist ingredients.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Divide between two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Add sliced bananas, chopped nuts, crushed pineapple and sweetened strawberries
to dissolved Jell-O.
Pour 1/2 mixture in dish; let jell.
Top with sour cream.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture on top of cream.
Let refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: 16 marshmallows, 1 cup crushed pineapple, melt together in a double boiler until clear, then add cool whip 1/2 pint whipping cream, add marshmallow mixture-pour in freezing tray, serve frozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Beat in cream cheese, then fold in Pet milk.
Add celery and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: great meat loaf
directions: My favorite thing to make is reservations for Sunday lunch at Ocademy Christian Academy.

title: orange creamsicle punch
directions: Pour soda over ice cream after stirring to mix.
Additional orange soda may be added to taste.
Garnish with orange slices. Makes a large punch bowl.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Saute onion, carrot and parsley in oil until soft.
Mix egg, ketchup, broth, hot pepper sauce and bread.

title: supreme chocolate cake
directions: Mix together (it's thick).
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside until topping is mixed.

title: marshmallow fudge(topping for ice cream)
directions: Mix brown sugar and cocoa in a 1-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Cook and stir until the mixture comes
to a boil. Cook rapidly for 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla. Cool for 5 minutes. Add marshmallows. Serve warm over vanilla ice cream. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: gloria's fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
(Mixture scorches easily.)
Remove from heat.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring beet juice to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Add Kool-Aid and Sure-Jell and bring to a boil again.
Add sugar and boil 3 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Trim with pimiento strips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, eggs and sugar.
Slowly add dry ingredients, nuts, vanilla and water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, cream and instant cocoa; boil at medium heat until small ball forms in cold water.
Add margarine, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan.
Yields about 20 pieces.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and chocolate.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in slightly greased 8 x 8-inch or 10 x 5-inch pan.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and broken cookies.
Mix together and chill.
Do not freeze.
I suggest cutting all ingredients in half for 4 or 5 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top the last 15 minutes of baking. Serves 10 to 12.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces and soak in the milk until very soft.
Break up any large pieces with a fork.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Break butter into small pieces and add to pudding.
Bake in buttered baking dish for about 30 minutes, or until firm at 325°.
Serve warm with Whiskey Sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, then tear into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients except stuffing together in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix grated Cheddar cheese with cream cheese.
Mix in dry salad dressing mix. Shape into ball or log and roll in pecans and cracker crumbs or chili powder.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Mix all except fruit together then stir in fruit.
Pour in a prepared pie shell.

title: three cheese potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until potato mixture is puffed and evenly browned on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain, add taco mix, water and tomato sauce. Cook for about 3 minutes and then add refried beans.
Cook 5 more minutes.
In 12 to 15-inch pan, place crushed chips, then add meat mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, green onions (if desired) and top with sour cream.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add well beaten eggs and milk.
Sift flour, salt, cocoa and baking powder together.
Sift twice.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven until cake tests done.
Use Cream Filling between layers.
Use Mother's Mocha Icing on top and sides.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onions.
Drain off half of the liquid.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for about 25 or 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: baked cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
Mix all ingredients together;
spoon into a 1qt. casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese has melted.
Stir before serving.
Serve hot with toasted bread or tortilla chips.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent rolls out into 12 x 18-inch baking sheet to form crust.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix cream
cheese,
yogurt and Ranch mix and spread onto cooked crust.
Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes.
Slice vegetables thinly and
press
into
cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover
and
refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Drain off most of fat.
Add onion to remaining fat and cook over medium heat until onion is yellow.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together and press in long pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: noncaustic drain opener
directions: Pour in order, the soda, salt and then vinegar into drain. Wait about 15 minutes, then flush drain thoroughly with boiling water.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Place steak in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place sliced onion over the top of steak and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together evaporated milk and soup. Pour over steak and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Cook in a skillet until brown.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Season with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle each with celery salt and paprika.
Place in bottom of crock-pot.
In medium bowl mix mushroom soup, celery soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cook 8 to 10 hours on low setting.
Serve over rice.
Serve with broccoli and hot rolls.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs, then add milk, vanilla and butter.
Last fold in pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: ravioli
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.

title: bohemian chocolate cookies
directions: Whirl walnuts in food processor, using short, on-off bursts, until almost powdery.
Or, use a nut grinder to grind finely.
Set aside.
Whirl chocolate in food processor or blender until powdery.
Set aside.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut chuck
beef into 1/4-inch cubes.
Brown the beef in the margarine, seasoned with pepper, in a cast-iron Dutch oven or a deep
covered
skillet.
Peel
and
cut onions in halves lengthwise.
Shave
them
very thin to give almost transparent slices, so that
when dish is finished there is not a trace of onion except
the
flavor.
Add
onion
to meat cubes and stir constantly until
thoroughly browned.
Add salt, 3 cups water, brown sugar
and
bay
leaves.
Cover
and simmer for an hour. Remove bay
leaves, then thicken gravy with the flour mixed to a smooth
paste
with 6 tablespoons water.
Cook until thickened. Serve
inside
of
a
ring of mashed potatoes.
I use a large Pyrex
dish,
about
2 to 2 1/2-inch deep.
Make a green vegetable salad and you have a yum yum meal.

title: upside down cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, 3/4 cup milk and Crisco. Beat 2 minutes on medium.
Add egg yolks, 1/2 cup milk, and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Butter and flour a 9x13 pan.
Pour cherries on bottom of pan.
Pour cake batter over cherries.

title: pasta and vegetable toss
directions: In large skillet, cok and stir onion, garlic and Italian seasoning in oil until onion is tender.
Add water, bouillon and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Toss with hot fettucini.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings with 287 calories, 0 mg cholesterol, 5 g fat and 481 mg sodium.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Place apples and cinnamon in microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Mash apples or whirl in blender.
Sweeten to taste, if desired.

title: chess (cheese) cake
directions: Mix well and press in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: brides punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool Aid in cold water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Combine dissolved jello, drink mix and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.
Add 7 - Up and sherbet. Serve immediately.

title: brownie peanut butter bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg. Beat well with spoon.
Fill paper-lined mini muffin cups about 1/2 full.
Press one peanut butter cup into batter in each cup.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brownies set.
Cool completely.

title: curried corn with red peppers
directions: In a saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Add sweet pepper and cook, stirring until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add curry powder, salt, pepper and cream.
Add corn; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Tastes great with ham steak.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together.
Cook until threads.
Add peanuts and stir continuously.
Cook until syrup mixture turns light brown.
Remove from heat; add soda, salt and butter.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread as thin as possible.

title: sauce for grilled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients and brush on shrimp.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, eggs and bananas.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake for 60 to 90 minutes at 350°.

title: pig cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Add oranges and beat until pieces are small.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: a polish farewell to lent
directions: Place kielbasa in a large pot; cover with water.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 45 minutes.
Add sauerkraut.
Continue to simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with horseradish or mustard.
Serves 14 people.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger together until crumbled, drain excess grease. In crockpot, met cheeses. Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onions, mix well. Makes a large amount and can be frozen. Serve with chips. Serves many.

title: date nut balls (humdingers)
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and dates.
Bring to boil and stir.
Remove from heat and cool 6 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll in small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
These freeze well and are special with my family each Christmas.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cook meat; add salsa.
Heat 5 minutes.
Add onions and spices. Divide mixture into fourths.
Put meat on tortillas and top with 1 ounce of cheese each.
Roll.
Spray baking pan with Pam and place chimichangas into pan.
Spray tops with Pam and bake at 475° for approximately 20 minutes (until tops are brown).

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Topping:
Melt butter in a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange cherries and nuts in bottom of pan.
Cover with brown sugar and then pineapple.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order and bake at 350°.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with chips, crackers or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a deep skillet, brown meat and drain off fat. After draining fat, add soup, water and rest of ingredients; stir well. Lower heat when steam appears. After lowering heat, allow to cook for 35 minutes. Stir often.

title: quick grape juice
directions: Put 1 cup grapes into scalded quart jar; add 1/2 cup sugar and fill to within 1/2 inch of top with boiling water.
Repeat 6 times. Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 quarts.
To serve, pour through tea strainer.

title: pineapple skillet cake
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar together in a heavy skillet until sugar is melted; cool.
Arrange pineapple slices over mixture. Beat sugar into eggs; add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt (all sifted together).
Mix and pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
While hot, turn out upside down on serving plate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: potluck chicken casserole
directions: Parboil chicken breasts. Saute onion in butter. Boil the linguine. Cut up chicken. Mix with chicken soup. Add Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper. If needed, add a little broth from chicken to moisten. Crumble crackers on top. Heat.

title: capri sandwich
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Place cut side up on a baking sheet.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 30 seconds or until lightly browned.
Rub garlic on cut sides of bread halves.
Discard garlic.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar with flour.
Add hot water.
To this mixture add milk. Add beaten egg yolks (use egg whites for meringue).
Add margarine or butter.
This will melt as mixture heats.
Cook until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and pour into a baked pie shell. Meringue:
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat again.
Place on pie filling and bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: chicken and dumpling recipe
directions: Boil chicken and remove from stock.
Mix together the flour and boiling chicken broth.
This makes wet dough.

Put 1 1/2 cups flour on bread board and as soon as the dough is cool enough to handle, work in the flour. Roll a little thicker than pie dough and cut into 1 or 2-inch strips. Turn them over and let dry for about 15 minutes.
Saute 1 diced onion in butter and add this to boiling broth. Drop in dumplings and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Boil the rhubarb, sugar and pineapple hard for 20 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Roll into balls and then roll in coconut.

title: enchilada chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the soups, milk, chicken, enchilada sauce and chilies; mix well. Cook until heated through. Garnish with sour cream. Yields approximately 7 servings.

title: ranch dip
directions: In blender or food processor, pour all cottage cheese and blend until smooth and creamy.
Blend about 5 minutes longer after getting smooth and creamy.
Add no fat sour cream and blend until mixed well.
Add dry dressing mix and blend together.
Can use with raw vegetables or on baked potato.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; add grated cheese.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to butter and cheese mixture.
Knead with fingers or electric mixer.
Put through a cookie press using star or ribbon mold.
Place on buttered-greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
You may cut them the desired length before or after baking (before may be better).
You may roll out and cut dough into strips if you don't have cookie press.

title: tamale pie
directions: Spray baking dish; line with corn tortillas.
Add layer of mixture; top with cheese and layer again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cook-out stew
directions: Add enough water to cover carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add peas and hot dogs; cook 10 minutes. Stir in soup and cheese and heat.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour to dry or microwave on paper towel for 2 minutes on High.
They dry faster.

title: mustard fish
directions: Combine equal parts of sour cream and mustard. Will need about 2 tablespoons of each per pound of fish. Crush the crackers. Cut fish into 2-inch chunks. Squirt the fish with lemon juice; dip into sauce, then roll in cracker crumbs, pressing to adhere to fish. Chill 2 hours (helps coating adhere in cooking process). Fry in hot oil until golden. Drain and serve while hot.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a Bundt or angel food pan with margarine.
Pour 1/2 cup pecans in bottom of pan.
Add frozen rolls.
Sprinkle rolls with brown sugar and butterscotch pudding (dry).
Sprinkle a generous amount of cinnamon over all ingredients.
Pour melted margarine evenly over rolls.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup pecans.
Let rise at room temperature for 8 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Invert on a plate immediately after removing from oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli, then add cooled broccoli. Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed cheese crackers (Cheez-Its).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and shortening to boiling point. Remove from heat. Add flour. Stir and let cool. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly. Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 360° for 45 minutes. DON'T open door. Cool. Split and fill with whipped cream or ice cream and coat with chocolate syrup.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add the remaining ingredients. Drop on wax paper.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Brown with chopped onion.
Brown ground beef with the mixture.
Add pork and beans and rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour into baking
dish.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first five items in large bowl.
Let set for an hour or so to partially thaw.
Then add half of the margarine. Pour into large shallow casserole.
Bake one hour covered with aluminum foil.
Then add rest of margarine to corn flakes and put on top of casserole.
Bake for another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage with dressing.
Toss with other ingredients and serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crock pot swiss chicken casserole
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Arrange chicken breasts in crock-pot and top with Swiss cheese, layering if necessary.
Mix soup and milk and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Mix onion in soup and pour over rice.
Mix well.
Place chicken over rice. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes, dot chicken with mayo.

title: cabbage and carrot slaw
directions: Combine vegetables in non-metallic container with cover.
To make dressing, mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Keeps well.
Serves 4.

title: apple snacks
directions: Cut apples into
wedges. Cut out core and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Place
in
single
layer
in flat microwave-safe plate. Cover with wax paper
and
microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes until
apples are tender.
Drain.
Combine peanut butter, honey and cinnamon.
Spread
thin
layer of mixture on apple wedges and serve.

title: layered salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Layer all items in a bowl the night before (or morning of) serving.
Vegetables should be patted dry.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: In 1 pint casserole mix sugar and cornstarch; blend in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Stir in cranberries.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Stir in apples and extract.
Turn into two 1 cup baking dishes.
In bowl combine oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of fruit.
Cook until apples are tender (3 1/2 minutes).

title: hot dog stir-fry
directions: Warm up cut hot dogs in nonstick skillet.
In a small bowl, drain juice from fruit.
Juice should total about 1 cup.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, ginger and cornstarch.
Mix until dissolved, then pour into skillet over hot dogs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until mixture is hot and bubbly and starting to thicken up.
Add pineapple; stir and heat until pineapple is hot. Add mandarin oranges, stirring very gently.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together, cover and refrigerate.

title: homemade vanilla extract
directions: Drop 2 whole vanilla beans into a liter of vodka.
Cap and let stand for 1 month.
Use in any recipe that calls for vanilla extract.

title: low-fat french toast
directions: Combine milk with egg substitute, lite salt and vanilla.
Add sweetener and cinnamon for alternate flavor, if desired.
Spray skillet with nonstick spray.
Heat.
Dip diet bread in egg mixture, then onto hot skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Top with sugar free syrup.
Serves 1.
Contains 115 calories, 9.1 g protein, 2 g fat, 2 mg chol.
and 275 mg sodium.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Form into 1/2 to 1-inch diameter balls.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm with cocktail sauce for dipping.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Set aside to cool while making second layer.

title: easy cherry pudding
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk, mix until well blended.
Pour over melted butter, do not stir.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup sugar over cherries.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Mix bananas, lemon juice and some pineapple juice in blender. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Freeze at least 2 to 3 days.
Let thaw for 5 to 7 hours until slushy.
Makes 20 servings.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Bring the following to a boil:

water, margarine and shortening. Mix flour and yeast and set aside. Add the remaining to the liquid. Mix all liquid with the dry ingredients in mixer. Add more flour, if necessary. Can be put in refrigerator overnight. Roll into 3 circles and cut each circle into 12 wedges and roll up each one, starting at the wide end, and put tip end down on a greased pan. Let rise in a moderately warm place for about 3 hours. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey oatmeal muffins(low-fat)
directions: Combine oats, both flours, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine milk, egg substitute, honey and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon in muffin pan coated with vegetable cooking spray, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 12 muffins.
Contains approximately 132 calories per muffin and 7 grams fat.
These cupcakes will be small but filling.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Drain and cool broccoli.
Mix broccoli, soup, milk, salt, pepper, rice, onion and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into baking dish and use rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain away grease. Add all the other ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar and Crisco.
Reserve 1/2 cup for crumbs.
Mix molasses, egg, hot water and dissolved baking soda and add to crumb mixture.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
"Lots of goo".

title: fried cabbage
directions: In a large skillet or frying pan, brown cut up bacon until crisp, add onion and cook just until the onion softens and becomes translucent.
Add shredded cabbage, water and soy sauce and cover and let cook for about 30 - 45 minutes until the cabbage is soft. Stir occasionally while cooking and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: snappy glazed meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, bread crumbs and salt; mix well. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake until brown.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly; add to meatballs in a chafing dish or crock-pot.

title: fiesta salad(good diabetic recipe)
directions: Cut red peppers in half and remove seeds.
Place on a broiling pan and flatten.
Broil 6 inches below heat for 8 minutes or until charred.
Allow to cool, then peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Mix everything except shrimp to a smooth paste with electric beater.
Cut shrimp into small chunks and stir in by hand. Prepare a day in advance.
Serve on assorted crackers.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; add margarine and seasonings, then egg. Mix and shape into balls around the marshmallows.
Dip in crushed graham crackers and fry in hot oil.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute bell pepper and onions until tender and set aside.
Cook cabbage in boiling water until leaves are tender.
Break leaves apart.
Mix ground beef, rice, bell pepper, onion, salt and pepper and 1/2 can of sauerkraut.

title: overnight tossed salad
directions: Layer in order given:
lettuce, celery, peppers and onions, cauliflower flowerets, peas, bacon and Cheddar cheese in large dish.
Top with mayonnaise, brown sugar and dry mustard. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Brown meat, salt and pepper to taste.
In casserole dish, layer tortillas, onion, cheese, meat and chiles.
Repeat until used up.
Blend soups and milk together and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can add grated cheese on top and heat until melted.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Mash the avocados.
Combine all ingredients except the tortilla chips in a large bowl, mixing well.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Chill until ready to serve.
Leave the two avocado pits in the guacamole until ready to serve.
This prevents discoloration.
Serves 6.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Blend chocolate wafer crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press into a 9 or 10-inch pie plate and chill at least 1 hour before filling.

title: chicken spinach salad
directions: Cut chicken into strips against the grain.
Pull stems from spinach and tear leaves.
Peel and section oranges.
Cut radishes and onion into thin slices.
Shake vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Pour dressing over spinach and chicken combination.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni 5 minutes to remove grease.
Drain.
Saute onion in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter until golden brown.
Place remaining butter in baking dish.
Toss spaghetti in butter.
Cover spaghetti with 1 can tomato sauce.
Add 1/2 of the Swiss cheese, 1/2 of the Mozzarella, all the mushrooms and onions.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese and pepperoni.
Add second can tomato sauce and rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn and peanuts together.
Bring sugar, syrup and honey to a boil.
Stir constantly until it boils, then boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour this mixture over the popcorn.
Stir and let cool in shallow pan.
After cooled, break into pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt over medium heat to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: squash dressing
directions: Moisten the bread crumbs with water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
If too thick, add more water until mixture pours easily into a greased or sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and set.

title: banana split pie
directions: Dip bananas in lemon or pineapple juice to prevent darkening. Combine powdered sugar, eggs and margarine and beat with an electric mixer about 5 minutes until fluffy.
Add grated chocolate and mix well.
Thinly slice two bananas and arrange in cooled, baked shell.
Pour mixture in shell.
Top with one sliced banana arranged around the rim of the pie to form border.
Chill 2 hours. Just before serving, top with whipped dessert topping and chopped nutmeats.

title: microwave rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart microproof casserole. Cover and place in oven. Cook on 100% power for 5 minutes.
Cook on 50% power for 13 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir through before serving.

title: sugar-free brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat vigorously until well blended. Spread mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Serves 16.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into large pieces.
Place in a 2-quart baking pan.
Pour butter over potatoes; toss until they are well coated.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: martian cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix well, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: potato-squash casserole
directions: Spread the onions in a 9 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Alternate slices of potato and squash, standing on edge, to fill the casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Pour the broth over the entire surface, slowly, so that the flour is moistened. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until tender, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain off most of fat and add flour to thicken.
Add sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour while hot over cut up boiled potatoes and onion.
Let set for hours before serving, perhaps overnight.
Serve warm.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan, heat apple juice and cinnamon stick to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl.
Makes 16 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Put in 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole and cook 35 minutes at 350°.
This makes its
own crust.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ingredients. Pour batter into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes. Cool and cut 24 pieces.

title: kahlua
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 1 quart of water to a boil, then add coffee.
Remove from heat.
In a separate saucepan, bring the other quart of water to a boil; add sugar and stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Mix both water mixtures together and let sit until cool.
When cool, add vanilla and pure grain alcohol and mix. Pour into a gallon container and store in a dark place for 2 weeks to ferment.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
May be doubled for 5-quart crock-pot.

title: dream pie squares
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers, if needed.
Blend milk and pudding mix.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl.
Reserve a few orange sections for garnish; dice remaining oranges and fold into mixture with nuts.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then remaining pudding mixture.
Garnish with orange sections and mint leaves.
Chill for 4 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: healthy apple salad
directions: Peel and core apples.
Crumble granola bars or use granola cereal.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside.
In another bowl beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Stir in strawberries and pecans. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together milk and pudding mix. After thickened, blend in Cool Whip.
Add creamed mix to pudding mix.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all vegetables in large bowl in any proportion with more tomatoes than other veggies.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Add parsley to taste and place all ingredients in sealed bowl in fridge overnight.
Serve cold by dipping vegetables out of marinade in slotted spoon.
Good for 2 days.
Is best if fresh garden veggies are used.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook the onions and green pepper in a little oil until yellow. Add the hamburger. Cook over medium heat until well blended.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish with lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Take cover off and cook 20 minutes longer to brown.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Stir until jello has melted.
Set aside until cooled.
After cooled, mix in Kool-Aid, cold water, pineapple juice and 7-Up.
After that is mixed well, add sherbet. It is best to put sherbet out 1 to 2 hours before ready to use so that it will be half melted.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto greased griddle.

title: leona's ice cream
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Put into ice cream maker can. Crushed fruit may be added.
Finish filling can with whole milk. Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers in a buttered dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms-alpine caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely. In medium pan, melt butter or margarine. Add stems and cook until tender. Add soup mix, bread crumbs, sherry and nuts; mix well. Fill caps and place on greased pan; sprinkle with cheese. Broil 5 minutes. These can be made ahead and frozen. Defrost slightly before broiling.

title: pistachio whip
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and optional ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour into large oblong dish 2 cans of peach pie filling. Sprinkle 1 box of dry yellow cake mix over peaches.
Melt 2 sticks of oleo and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut over top.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 cup of nuts over coconut.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: california pecan roll(microwave)
directions: In a microwave-proof container, put morsels, milk and vanilla and microwave until melted.
Take out and combine; add nuts. Chill.
Roll into 2 (5-inch long) rolls, 2 inches round.
Beat an egg white until frothy.
Frost rolls.
Cover roll completely with pecans.
Let dry, uncovered, overnight.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Give as a gift or slice and serve.

title: date nut loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and Karo to soft ball stage (240° on candy thermometer).
Let cool 3 minutes.
Add chopped dates.
Cook 5 minutes and stir well.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add pecans and vanilla.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch
thick.
Slice onions and place on potatoes in layered form
in
baking
dish.
Add
salt
and pepper to liking.	Slice butter on top of potatoes and onions. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover
with
foil,
then	take
out. Cover with paprika and bake 15 minutes more, uncovered.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Make into
small balls.
Put on baking sheet and bake 20 minutes.
These freeze well also.

title: kraut salad
directions: Squeeze and wring out all juice from kraut.
Cut pimento in fine strips.
Chop green pepper and celery.
Finely chop onion. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Place in covered container.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat potatoes with butter, eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid.
Dough should be soft yet firm enough to roll.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry at 375° until golden brown on both sides.
Makes about 5 dozen doughnuts and holes.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine first five ingredients in bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together in separate bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla and beat until well combined.

title: play doh
directions: Cook over medium heat until it glumps together, stirring constantly.
Knead while still warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter over low heat.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix well. Roll mixture into balls and cool.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until tender.
Add soup, diced Ro-Tel, cubed Velveeta and chicken.
Heat until cheese melts.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with pasta and cover with remaining 1/3.
Cook at 350° until hot and bubbly. Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: skillet beef italiano
directions: Brown beef in skillet, leaving meat in large chunks.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, oregano and vegetables.
Bring to a full boil. Separate vegetables and stir.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine oil and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir well and fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Put on wire rack to cool.

title: sausage and chicken gumbo
directions: Make roux.
Add water and seasonings (whatever you like).
Add all ingredients and cook for about 45 minutes.
Add rice and file.

title: julie's apple pie
directions: Place apples in bowl and mix sugar and spices. Let stand until juice appears, about 10 minutes. Prepare pie crust and put in 9-inch pie plate. Put apples in plate and top with top crust. Dot with butter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar. Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 8 minutes. Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Fold in the Dream Whip, prepared according to box directions, into the cream cheese mixture. Spread over cooled pretzel crust. Mix strawberry jello and water plus frozen strawberries. Cool. Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until congealed. Makes 18 to 20 pieces.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.
Will serve about 10 people.
Very good!

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and add 3/4 cup crumbled crackers, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Put in dish.
Top with cheese and stick in preheated oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: baked potato delights(bulvines bandukes)
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until done.
Cool, peel and mash.
Add flour and salt.
Roll out on floured board about 1-inch high.
Cut into 1-inch wide strips.
Cut each strip into 2-inch pieces.
Place in greased pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: the best cookie you ever ate!
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, oil, salt and vanilla. After measuring flour, sift together with the other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll dough into balls slightly smaller than a walnut.
Dough will be soft.
Roll ball in sugar.
Flatten with the bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Allow room for spreading.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or lightly browned in 350° oven. These cookies are not supposed to get brown.

title: spring green salad
directions: Wash and dry greens, place in a large bowl. Add chives and season with salt and pepper; drizzle over about 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Toss well to coat. Squeeze lemon juice over the greens and toss again. Taste and adjust seasoning. Serve immediately.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind the meat together.
Beat egg and combine with milk.
Let stand.
Add seasonings and meats.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook beef and onion
in skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain and wipe grease out of pan.
Add taco seasoning mix and water, stirring.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Spoon half of bean mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Top with half of meat mixture, half of cheese and all of corn chips.
Repeat layers with remaining bean mixture, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with sour cream, lettuce and tomato.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, onion, parsley, garlic, basil, oregano, mustard, black pepper, red pepper in a 4 cup measuring bowl. Reserve.
Place peas in a large bow.
Pour dressing over peas. Toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate overnight.
Toss once.
Line large platter with pepper rings and place peas in center.
May add cubed ham and cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes; stir in sour cream, then heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Layer refried beans in the bottom of a dish.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning together and put on top of the beans.
Chop up onions, tomato and black olives and put on top.
Top with grated cheese.

title: oreo chocolate chip mint dessert
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup crushed Oreos.
Mix remaining crushed Oreos with 1/4 cup melted margarine in bowl.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Chill.
Melt chocolate in heavy saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup margarine, sugar, salt and evaporated milk.
Boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; cool.
Spread over crust.
Chill in freezer until set.
Spread ice cream over chocolate layer. Sprinkle reserved Oreos over top.
Freeze in covered container until firm.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Heat and stir until melted.
Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix by hand until moistened.
Press half of this mixture on bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust; drizzle with melted caramels and crumble remaining cake mix mixture over all. Return to oven and bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator 30 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: tomato salad
directions: Bring soup to the boiling point; melt cream cheese in it. Stir until blended, then add gelatin, soaked in 1/2 cup water. Set away to cool, then add vegetables.
Serve on lettuce with a dressing.
Good served with saltine crackers.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in microwave in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir to mix.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula, press mixture evenly in pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: perfect roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cook 7 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off for 2 hours.
Do not open oven.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water, drain and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper; toss lightly.
Spoon half of potato mixture into lightly greased dish.
Top with half each of bacon and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in large nonstick frying pan to medium-high. Pound chicken breasts until thin or use flash-frozen chicken breasts, which are already thin. Dredge chicken in beaten egg, then dredge chicken in bread crumbs. Brown quickly in olive oil. While still very hot, cover chicken with lemon juice and wine. This will make a sauce and you will want a lot. Reduce heat to medium and cover. Allow to cook for at least 30 minutes. Cooking time may be up to an hour and will depend on the thickness of the chicken (the thinner the better) and how hot you cook it. Add broccoli, squash, onions, peppers, etc. to TOP of chicken for last 20 minutes of cooking time, if desired. Chicken should be very tender. Serve hot. Sauce can be served over the chicken or over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown chopped onion, chopped bell pepper and hamburger in frying pan.
In a large casserole dish, add the remaining ingredients and the browned hamburger and onion.
Cover very tightly.
(If not covered good, it will not get done.)
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When done, sprinkle grated cheese on top. Serves 6.

title: bacon spinach salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble; set aside.
Place greens and onions in a salad bowl; refrigerate until serving.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a jar and shake until well mixed.
Just before serving, pour dressing over greens. Toss well to coat.
Add bacon and toss.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Cook and drain Creamettes.
Brown beef, move to side of pan and saute onions.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Mix beef and onions.
Put layer of macaroni (about half) in bottom, then layer beef and onions.
Pour half can of corn over layers.
Then add layer of cheese over this.
Repeat all layers.
Pour can of tomato soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in round balls.
Pour diluted can of tomato sauce and 1 can of water over.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours. Keep covered until done.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and teaspoon of vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Next, add Rice Krispies and fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Grease baking sheet.)

title: good corn bread
directions: Pour into greased skillet and bake.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine, mix well and cool.
Set aside.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese. A dash of cayenne pepper is also suggested.
Mix well.
Stir in drained macaroni.
Spoon mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes. Uncover casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: glaze for colin's meat loaf
directions: Combine the above and carefully spread over the top of meat loaf, bake 10 min longer.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Add lemon juice (you must add lemon juice for the mixture to firm).
Add pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cool in fridge for a couple hours if you can wait that long.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 bag coconut.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan. Stir in water. Cook, stirring, over medium heat until thick and clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until soft mounds form.
Add remaining sugar gradually, beating well after each addition. Add cornstarch mixture.
Continue beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks. Mound onto cooled pie, sealing edges to pastry shell. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let pie cool at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: north dakota fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 2 well-greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add the rest of the ingredients. In separate small bowl, combine the following:

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Mix in large bowl garlic, basil, oregano, pepper, bread, egg white and ground meat.
Form large meatballs and stuff each with 1 teaspoon chopped pepperoni and 1 teaspoon chopped Mozzarella. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with waxed paper and coat the paper with shortening.
Mix until smooth the pumpkin, eggs, sugar, flour and soda.
Pour onto pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While hot, flip pan onto kitchen towel.
Remove the waxed paper and roll with towel like jelly roll.
Refrigerate one hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Put oil in skillet with small amount of corn meal and get hot. Pour some of the hot oil into the bread mix. Mix well and pour into skillet. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add cherry pie filling, Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: black bean chili(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: *Or use regular black beans, soaked and cooked.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter and stir in flour.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Place cooked cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce over cabbage and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top when done.
This recipe is supposed to make its own crust.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spray pan with Baker's Joy. Pour into a Bundt pan or tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake springs back to touch.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, water and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking without stirring until temperature reaches 280°.
Gradually stir in salted peanuts until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until temperature reaches 300°; remove from heat.
Add soda; blend quickly.
Turn out onto heavy buttered cookie sheet and spread evenly with spatula.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat the egg in a measuring cup.
Add the vinegar and enough water to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Cut shortening into flour until it resembles corn meal.
Make 4 holes in flour mixture and add liquid.
Mix quickly and lightly.
This makes 2 pies with 2 crusts or 4 or 5 single pie crusts.

title: squash and cheese souffle
directions: Cook and mash the squash, adding onion if desired.
(I cook mine in the microwave in the same casserole it will be served in. Add a tablespoon or two of water, cover and microwave until tender.)
Mix together the eggs, squash (and onion), cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with the crushed crackers.
Drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Good leftover, too!

title: sauteed apple rings
directions: Peel, core
and
slice apples.	Melt butter and stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add apples, tossing to coat.
Cover and cook on low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Mix gently, but well.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer on medium for 3 minutes. Bake on a 1-inch deep baking sheet.
Line sheet with wax paper and butter to avoid sticking.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool completely and slice into 4 equal layers; stack.
Ice between layers and top but not on sides of cake.

title: pork loin
directions: Rub pork loin with salt and lemon pepper. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°. Add pineapple, sweet and sour sauce, soy sauce and carrots. Continue to cook 30 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix all together in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix sugar, pretzels and melted butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain juice from corn. Add tomato, onion and pickle. Mix well with mayonnaise.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Drop in boiling broth.
Cover at least 5 minutes.
Uncover and boil until done, about 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and butter, mixing until blended.
Add sugar and spices; mix well.
Blend in eggs and milk, stirring well (batter should be a little thin).
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 350° until pies are pretty brown, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Combine and beat 2 minutes.

title: hearty beef-vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large pot or kettle.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add carrots and remaining vegetables.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: mini pancakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
In another mixing bowl, combine the buttermilk, egg and oil.
Add to the flour mixture all at once. Stir the mixture just until combined, but still slightly lumpy. Spray an unheated nonstick griddle or nonstick heavy skillet with nonstick coating.
For each pancake, pour about 1 tablespoon batter onto hot griddle or skillet.
Cook until pancakes are golden brown on both sides, turning when pancakes have bubbly surfaces and slightly dry edges, about 1 minute per side.

title: seafood pasta toss
directions: While pasta is hot, add oleo and all other cooked ingredients and toss together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Keep hot until served.

title: jalapeno hot cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, whip eggs and milk together.
Add all liquid ingredients.
Mix together salt, sugar, baking powder and meal. Add this to liquid mixture and mix well.
Stir in grated cheese. Pour into oiled 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This bread freezes well.
Cut into squares; wrap in foil to freeze.

title: joanne's microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and add peanuts and salt.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring at the end of 4 minutes.
After cooking 8 minutes, add margarine and vanilla and microwave on High, 1 to 2 minutes.
Then add soda and stir well and place on buttered cookie sheet.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bar cookies
directions: Melt 2 sticks of margarine in microwave or on top of stove. Add to graham cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Pat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cherry surprises
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Blend in flour and salt.
Add flavoring.
Pinch off pieces of dough and flatten in the palm of your hand.
Insert a cherry and completely cover with dough.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Stir in raisins, nuts and oats.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Make jello as per package, using pineapple juice.
Let settle until it shakes.
In the meantime, beat cream cheese with pineapple.
Add to partly settled jello.
Fold in Cool Whip and cherries.
You could add some nuts, if desired.

title: eleanor's island-style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving syrup.
In skillet, brown chicken in Crisco.
Pour off fat.
Add reserved syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple chunks. Cook 5 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally. Combine cornstarch and water.
Gradually stir in sauce. Cook, stirring until thickened. Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season to taste with pepper.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in two well-greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.

title: my family's fav pancakes
directions: Beat milk, soda, flour and sugar into egg.
Next, beat shortening, baking powder and salt.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.

title: greek rice pudding
directions: Place 6 cups milk, rice and sugar in a large saucepan.
Cover and heat over medium heat without stirring until it begins to steam, about 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, egg and flavorings thoroughly. Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover bowl and chill for about 2 or 3 hours.

title: cheesy tortilla dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: The verse is John 3:16.
To me this is truly the greatest message I have ever heard.
Oh, what I wouldn't give if I could get everyone to live this way.

title: hopi piki bread(traditional)
directions: Mix ash with boiling water; strain juniper ash into pot. Stir.
Add blue cornmeal.
Stir with wooden spoon or stick.
Let cool.
Spread on hot, greased griddle or stone with palm of hand. Be certain the layer is very thin.
Cook for a very short time. Carefully lift the paper thin layer from griddle by rolling from one end to the other jelly roll fashion.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Bottom Layer: Mix together the butter (melted), chopped pecans and coconut and place in 9 x 13 pan.

title: baby club sandwich
directions: Place chicken salad between 2 slices of bread and toast with butter in pan on low heat.
Toast other piece of bread the same on both sides.
After bread is toasted to a golden brown, spread mayonnaise on top of toasted chicken salad part.
Place 4 or 5 strips of bacon on this; add thin slices of tomato and lettuce. Salt and pepper.
Cut sandwich with sharp knife and hold together with toothpicks.

title: aunt margaret's shrimp salad
directions: Mix shrimp, cheese cut in 1/4 inch cubes, chopped olives, bacon bits and croutons.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, dill weed, poppy seed and garlic salt to taste.
Either spoon sauce over or fold in shrimp.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: *Let potatoes thaw about 30 minutes before starting to mix.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple, bring to a boil, and simmer 1 minute.
