Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Cook the meat; drain well.
Add cut up mushrooms (if desired) and seasoning.
Cut Velveeta cheese up and melt it in.
Spoon into bread slices.
Warm in a 350° oven for a few minutes until bread is slightly toasted.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all together; form in small balls and roll in pecans.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: tex-mex cornbread salad
directions: Crumble half of the prepared cornbread into the bottom of a large serving bowl. Top with half of the beans.

In another bowl, combine the tomatoes, onion, green pepper and jalapeno peppers. Blend well. Spread half of the vegetable mixture over the beans. Sprinkle on half of the bacon and half of the cheese. Stir together the sour cream and salsa.
Spread half of the dressing over the cheese. Repeat layering procedure with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with sour cream and jalapeno slices, if desired.
Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch chips and butter; cool for 10 minutes.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; add butterscotch mixture and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to batter and mix well.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts; spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: kugeli
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp.
Turn flame off.
Add butter and let melt.
Let sit while peeling and grating potatoes in a bowl or pan.
Pour all grated potatoes into rag.
Squeeze out almost all moisture into bowl.
Let this water sit for 10 minutes.
Spill off water leaving potato starch.
Add to this eggs, salt and can of milk.
Mix well.
Add squeezed potatoes; mix well.
Add bacon.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 2 x 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange salad dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool and add orange juice, oranges and pineapple.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set until solid.
Beat together and let set, the instant pudding and cup of milk.
Fold whipped topping into pudding.
Spread on gelatin mixture.
Let set in refrigerator.
Before serving, sprinkle with ground nuts.
Serves 12.

title: fresh cranberry pie
directions: Place cranberries in a well-buttered 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with nuts and 1/3 cup sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well, then pour over cranberry mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pot pie (turkey or chicken)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Combine soup, meat and vegetables. Place in a 9 inch pie plate. Mix remaining ingredients, pour over meat mixture. Bake 30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into tart shells and place on baking sheet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.
Let cool.
Makes 12 tarts.

title: ultimate sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and extract.
Stir in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well; refrigerate 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half. Roll out half on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Keep remaining half refrigerated.
Cut into shapes.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: red raspberry pudding
directions: Place frozen red raspberries in sieve over bowl to completely defrost.
Cream 2 tablespoons margarine with the sugar.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add it alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into 7 or 8-inch baking pan.
Place drained whole red raspberries over the batter.
Measure liquid drained from berries and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Combine liquid, remaining margarine and lime juice and bring just to a boil.
Pour over raspberries and batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a glass baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Put the butter in the dish and place in oven until melted.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the butter.
Drain peaches and place on top of batter.
Bake about 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: spanish asparagus and orange salad(heart healthy)
directions: Cook the asparagus in boiling salted water for 3 to 4 minutes, until just tender. Drain and refresh under cold water. Grate the zest from half an orange and reserve. Peel both the oranges and cut into segments. Squeeze out the juice from the membrane and reserve the juice. Put the asparagus, orange segments, tomatoes and lettuce into a salad bowl. Mix together the oil and vinegar and add 1 tablespoon of the reserved orange juice and 1 teaspoon of the zest. Season the dressing with salt and pepper. Just before serving, pour the dressing over the salad and mix gently to coat.

title: pan barbecue
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized pieces.
Sprinkle with tenderizer. Place in big pan; add rest of ingredients and bring to boil. Cover and simmer for several hours.
Have plenty of bread for good sopping!

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, until smooth.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve with thick potato chips or crackers.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.
Improves upon standing.

title: fried eggplant or squash
directions: Put sliced eggplant on wax paper and sprinkle each slice lightly with salt.
Let stand for at least an hour.
This will take the water out.
Use paper towel to get water off wax paper. Coat each slice with flour.
Fry in oil or shortening until browned.
Sprinkle each slice while hot with cheese.
Serve while still warm.

title: easy salt dough(kid's recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Add more water if needed. Knead into soft dough.
Model as with any dough.

title: cheese-bacon stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Leave oven on.
Saute bacon in skillet until crisp. Add mushrooms and green onion; cook 4 to 5 minutes until mushrooms are lightly cooked.
Transfer mixture to bowl.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop out flesh, leaving 1/2 inch on the skin.
In a bowl, mash potatoes until smooth.
Stir in mushroom mixture, Cheddar cheese, pepper, salt and butter.
Spoon back into potato skins. Place on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until piping hot.
Top each potato with sour cream and serve.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Needs a very large pot.

title: corn and noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain the noodles.
Mix noodles and all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: apple gingerbread cobbler
directions: Combine apples, brown sugar, 1 cup water, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cover and cook until apples are tender.

title: fluffy salmon loaf
directions: Remove bone from salmon, flake.
Mix salmon, salt, paprika, pepper, onion, cracker crumbs, butter and tomato juice.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple cheese wedgies
directions: Core apples and slice into wedges.
Cut cheese into 16 slices about same size as apple wedges.
Place a slice of cheese on each piece of apple and arrange in shapes on child's dish.
Serve with a glass of cold milk.
An apple a day will keep the doctor and dentist away.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place in the bottom of a casserole dish, after cutting up in small pieces.
Put stuffing mix in large bowl, pour milk over and let stand for about 15 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients and pour on top of chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: broiled grapefruit delight
directions: Place grapefruit on a boiler, cut side down.
Spread melted margarine evenly over grapefruit.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Broil 6-inches from heat, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Add slices of cooked chicken on top.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix well, except candy.
Add M&M's candy.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.

title: lazy enchiladas(no meat)
directions: Mix tomato soup, eggs, salt and chili powder.
Prepare cheese and onion; mix together in a large bowl.
Fix lettuce and sprinkle a bed on platter or plate.
In a large pan, heat oil on medium heat.
Start with 3 tablespoons and add as needed.
It requires 1 teaspoon per tortilla.
Dip tortillas quickly into the soup sauce and fry 1 1/2 minutes on each side only until edge is cooked. Remove tortilla quickly and sprinkle with cheese and onion mixture and roll up.
Set in Pyrex square or oblong dish.
Repeat tortilla with mixture and roll up until all are done.
Keep hot in warm oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Transfer to the lettuce bed.
Decorate with sliced tomatoes.
Serves 6. Takes about 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients except cheeses and tortillas.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan and layer first sauce, then tortillas and cheeses.
Next layer begin with tortillas, sauce and cheeses.
Use all ingredients. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool a few minutes before cutting.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cheeses and sugar until smooth, add pineapple, chopped cherries and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Pour in container and place in freezer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package; drain corn and pour condensed soup over corn in dish.
(Do not add water to soup.) Cut cheese in small cubes and mix together.
Pour cooked rice over mixture and stir.
Place in oven until cheese melts.
Ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Add corn meal, garlic salt and soda.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred cheese together and add other ingredients.
Mix together and form a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap until set.
Roll in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cool for 24 hours.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter (reserve). Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs on low speed until moistened. Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of reserved crumb mixture.
Spread remaining batter evenly over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes (until wooden pick comes out clean).
Cool.

title: cheddar cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine baking mix and cheese.
Combine eggs and milk; add to cheese mixture, mixing just enough to moisten.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger and taco seasoning together.
Drain off fat. Mix hamburger with tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup and milk until blended.
May use nonfat sour cream. Put a small amount of mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Divide the meat mixture between the 12 flour tortillas with a little grated cheese in each one.
Roll up and place in pan.
Pour the remaining cream mixture over the top of the flour tortillas and top with green chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This also is good with chicken.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Cool and frost.
Do not grease and flour pan.

title: spaghetti sauce(makes 10 to 12 quarts)
directions: Put all the ingredients in a large kettle and boil moderately for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often so it won't scorch.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts. Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg, then add the dissolved yeast to egg mixture.
Then add 2 cups of warm water and add enough flour to make soft dough.
Make out rolls like biscuits and let rise, then bake.
Dough can be refrigerated about 2 weeks.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Force sauce through fine strainer to remove seeds.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Soak fruit overnight in whiskey and vanilla.
Mix other ingredients with this.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325°.
Cut fruit and pecans in small pieces.

title: impossible chicken-n-broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion in greased pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Beat together oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, 2 at a time; add vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in syrup, flour, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan at 350° until done.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Saute celery, onions and pepper in margarine in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add beef and cook until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Stir in mushrooms, corn and the rest of the ingredients.
Add noodles; spoon mixture into a greased deep three-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, three minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake well and refrigerate.

title: tasty zucchini relish
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the ground zucchini and ground onion. Let stand overnight, drain, rinse with water and add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Put all of this in a gallon jar and finish filling up with water.
Stir.

title: potato-vegetable scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place dried potatoes from mix in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the envelope of sauce mix from package.
Top with frozen mixed vegetables, onion and celery seed.
Pour boiling water over all; stir until well combined.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender, about 35 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and vanilla for 3 minutes in large saucepan.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour cooked mixture into oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
With large spoon, stir thoroughly.
Pour out on a cookie sheet.
Cut into squares before hard.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown deer pieces in 1 tablespoon oil until no longer pink. Cover the meat with water and boil until tender (about 1 hour). Add potatoes, carrots, mixed vegetables and onion; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce; cook 10 more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until ice cubes are crushed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab crostini
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Line a broiler pan with foil.
Pick over the crabmeat to remove any cartilage.
In a medium bowl, combine the crabmeat, bell pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, cheese and hot pepper sauce.
Blend well.
Spread 1 tablespoon crab mixture on each slice of bread.
Place the crostini on the broiler pan and broil 4-inches from the heat for 5 to 6 minutes or lightly browned.

title: onion souffle
directions: Ensure that the cream cheese is softened and onions are thawed and drained of all liquid.
Combine all ingredients and cook at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: meat balls creole
directions: Mix together beef, rice, chopped celery, black pepper, garlic salt and basil; shape into balls.
Place in a baking dish.

title: honey pickles
directions: Boil ingredients together except cucumbers; let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cucumbers.
Return to heat; let cook until cucumbers lose their bright color.
Pack in clean jars and seal.

title: campfire pork
directions: In
a
5-quart
Dutch
oven,
combine
all ingredients, except water.
Simmer
for
1 1/2 hours.
Add a little wine if it gets too dry.
Add water and simmer 1 1/2 hours more.
When meat starts to
fall
apart, remove lid and simmer most of the moisture away. Serve in tacos, tostadas or use in enchiladas.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the brown sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and measure.
Take out 1 cup for dusting cut up fruit.
Sift the rest with the spices and dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture, fruit and nuts alternately with molasses and wine to egg and butter mixture. Mix well, using a large bowl.
Hands do the best job.

title: blue fantasy
directions: In order listed, add ingredients to cake pan.
Cook at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced apple and walnut cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: all vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Melt butter.
Mix with cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Dissolve well.
Then add crushed pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate until firm.
Add milk to instant pudding. Stir until mixed.
Add to Cool Whip.
Mix well, then spread over chilled jello and serve.

title: poor man's crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 8-inch dish, place fish.
Mix together all the ingredients and sprinkle on top of fish.
Combine 1/2 cup of remaining stuffing mix and 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of fish mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: hominy and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until smooth.
Add milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Add salt, pepper, onion and chili powder; stir well.
Wash and drain hominy.
Stir in and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti al olio
directions: Put all sauce ingredients in frypan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Then mash with fork to break up anchovies and capers. Add 1/3 cup of water and let cook, slowly, about 15 to 20 minutes. (Don't burn that garlic.)
Pour over cooked spaghetti with lots of grated cheese.
(May want to save a little boiled water from spaghetti to add if dish is too dry, as grated cheese is drying.
I usually don't need the extra water.)

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Lightly grease 10 x 1 1/2 pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds on high or 1 minute by hand. Pour into plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: gourmet beef noodle casserole
directions: Saute beef with onion in oil; drain.
Stir next 8 ingredients in and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles. Beat together cottage cheese and sour cream and add to noodles. Pour one cup of meat mixture into a 3-quart casserole and add a layer of noodles and a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce and a little cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Mix together and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If you like French fried onions (from a can), they are good sprinkled over this.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Mix together in casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°. Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender. Serve over rice.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream sugar and butter; blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, chopped cherries and pecans.
Form dough into 3-inch balls and roll in flaked coconut.
Wrap dough in wax paper and chill. Place dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: crisp coconut bran cookie
directions: Beat first four ingredients together (all by hand).
Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Delish!

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole dish greased with oleo for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: jello gelatin jigglers(family size recipe)
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water or juice.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm or about 3 hours.

title: rich recipe cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease completely Bundt pan and flour lightly.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool about 3 minutes in pan after removing from oven.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Place broccoli (thawed) on the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch dish. Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Spread on a layer of cheese and top with buttered crumbs.
Repeat layer of cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips in well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and potato chips combined on top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam the squash and onion until done. Mash the squash and onion and mix everything (except the dressing) in the squash mixture. Pour into an 8 x 10-inch dish. Pour dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: st. ursula faculty punch
directions: Mix all together and pour into punch bowl.
Make a ring of frozen orange crush to float on top.
Serves 18 to 22 people

title: strawberry figs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 15 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars.
Quick and easy, tastes like strawberry preserves.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in the pineapple juice.
Bring pineapple, sugar and lemon juice to a boil.
Add this to gelatine mixture. Set aside until it starts to jell.
Grate the cream cheese and whip the cream until stiff.
Add to gelatine when it thickens.
Will serve about 20.

title: mountain pound cake
directions: Cream
oleo, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix baking powder in flour.
Add
alternately
with
milk, then add flavorings. Mix well.
Pour
in
greased tube pan.	Put in cold oven!
Set temperature at 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open the oven, not even once!

title: rock candy
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.

title: aunt rose's meat loaf(75 year old recipe)
directions: Add all ingredients into bowl and hand mix.
Put tomato juice and egg in last.
Shape into loaf in nongreased pan.
Add potatoes.
If desired, put bacon strips on top (3 slices).
Bake in 350° to 345° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Judge by softness of potatoes around loaf.

title: pasta and black-eyed peas
directions: Saute onion, carrot, garlic and parsley in olive oil until soft, but not brown.
Add peas, undrained, and all spices and seasonings.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine milk and oats and let stand at least 5 minutes.
Add oil and eggs, mixing well.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir only until moistened.
Bake on hot lightly oiled griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Makes 10 to 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; beat on medium with mixer.
Add eggs, syrup and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Add the salt, soda and the oats.
Mix with a metal spoon and stir well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
The dough will be stiff.
Pack the dough into a 1/4 cup measuring cup and drop 4 inches apart on a foil-lined or greased cookie sheet.
Press into 3 1/2-inch cookies with fingers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Center of cookies will be slightly soft.
Cool slightly on the cookie sheet.
Remove to a wire to cool completely.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and 1/3 cup powdered sugar well.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 1 hour or until bottoms are slightly browned.
Roll in confectioners sugar immediately and let cool. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Combine
shortening, sugar and egg.
Cream these ingredients. Put
baking
soda
in pulp and set.
Add pulp to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts to flour mixture.	Combine all and drop
by teaspoon
onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nana's eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with 1 cup of the sugar.
Stir in milk and liquor (or extract).
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into milk and yolk mixture. Beat whipping cream and fold in.
Chill several hours.
Serve with freshly grated nutmeg.
Serves about 20.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and pineapple with juice in medium bowl; stir well.
Gently fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts into pudding mix.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour in casserole or mold; chill until set.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Put in pot with chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Put mixture in blender and puree.
(For best soup, leave it chunky with bits of potatoes when blending.)
Put mixture back into pot; add cream and butter.
Cook until warm.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Brown the ground meat, add onion that has been cut in small pieces and garlic cut small and parsley. Brown and add tomato sauce and canned tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: grilled tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle tomato halves with salt and pepper and crumbs.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Empty sour cream in a bowl.
Measure marshmallows in the sour cream container and add to sour cream.
Add the rest of the ingredients, stirring gently and well.
Chill several hours.

title: jan hagles
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and spices in medium bowl.
Beat butter and sugars in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour until blended.
Stir in almonds.
Shape dough into 8 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch brick.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Cut brick into 1/8-inch slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
These cookies taste like the Dutch windmill cookies that you can buy.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/8-inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. In large skillet, heat oil and add steak, chopped onion and minced garlic and brown.
Add sliced pieces of pepper and bouillon. Cover and simmer until cooked.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes more.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and water and add to cooked steak and peppers.
Cook until liquid is thickened.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: onion soup(crock-pot)
directions: Saute onions in covered skillet until soft.
Uncover; add salt and sugar.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook for 3 minutes longer.
Combine onions, stock and wine in cooker.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with toasted rounds of French bread topped with cheese.
If you have earthenware bowls, fill with soup.
Top with toasted bread.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under preheated broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.
Or you can toast the bread, sprinkle with cheese, broil and then place on top of soup served in standard soup bowls.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake with nut icing
directions: Combine sugar and salad oil together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beat after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix well. Add nuts and carrots.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, remove and ice.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime solution for 24 hours.
Rinse and cover with fresh water.
Soak 3 hours.
Drain well.
Cover with vinegar and sugar mix.
Soak overnight, then boil gently 40 minutes or until clear.
Place in jar and seal.

title: simple simon bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with crumbs; press firm.
Spread with coconut flakes; cover with chocolate chips, then with butterscotch chips.
Spread with nut meats.
Drizzle condensed milk over whole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as dip or with meal.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine the ground beef, rice and onion in a large bowl.
Mix. Form the mixture into balls.
Place the balls in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine the soup, water and Worcestershire sauce in a medium bowl.
Pour the sauce over the balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: david's brownies
directions: Melt butter in large pan. Add cocoa and sugar. Remove from heat. Add eggs, mixing well. Add vanilla and salt then flour. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut-date balls
directions: Beat thoroughly eggs, sugar and dates.
Cook, stirring constantly, 10 minutes.
Add the cereal and pecans.
Chill thoroughly.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Stir in eggs, vanilla, salt, soda and flour.
Roll in balls.
Press with fork (dipped in flour) first one way, then the other way.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: baccala(codfish)
directions: In a large 3-quart heavy saucepan, place butter and oil.
Heat until butter melts.
Add remaining ingredients except codfish. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and add fish, partially thawed and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot polenta or potatoes.

title: chocolate-coconut pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into uncooked pie crusts (2 crusts).
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple and carrots by hand.
Add 2 cups flour sifted with baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Sift in part of last cup flour; add nuts or raisins, then rest of flour.
Mix well.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf bread pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Good with or without frosting.
Cake is moist and tasty and freezes well.

title: "kristus"(european recipe)

Cut
oleo into flour, add eggs to make stiff dough
(as	for
pie
dough).
Roll

board 1/8-inch thick.
Cut
into
4 x 1-inch strips.
Slit center of each strip and fold
end into center.	Fry in hot fat, about 2 minutes each side.
Immediately	remove	from
oil and roll in powdered sugar; allow to cool and enjoy.
Nice for Christmas.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix well the cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup butter.
Line bottom of baking dish with 1 cup buttered crumbs.
Add asparagus. Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover with cheese sauce made from remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over cheese sauce.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: angel-pudding layered dessert
directions: In a large glass bowl or punch bowl, place a layer of cubed angel food cake.
Place a layer of chocolate pudding.
Place a layer of lite Cool Whip.
If desired, you may add fat-free cream cheese to the Cool Whip.
Add a layer of broken Hershey's with almonds nuggets or Hershey's cookies 'n mint nuggets.
Layers may be repeated as desired and garnished with chopped pecans.

title: long johns
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening to the milk and let cool.
Add yeast to the water (the water must be boiled first or the yeast won't react).
Proceed as with bread, adding 2 eggs and nutmeg; mix in a ball and let it rise until double in bulk.
Knead down and roll to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut and let rise for 30 to 40 minutes.
Deep fry at 375°.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: southern parmesan fried chicken
directions: Add and mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and add some milk.
Dip chicken in egg and milk, then cover with dry mixture.
Redip in egg and milk mixture and then cover again with dry mixture.
Fry chicken in oil on stove and cook until done. Serve with vegetable of choice.

title: tomato corn bake
directions: Cut tomatoes in halves crosswise.
Remove seeds and most of pulp from centers.
Sprinkle cavities with salt.
Combine corn, cheese and onions.
Firmly pack into each tomato shell.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cook, uncovered in microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High.
In oven, bake 20 to 30 minutes, until heated thoroughly.
